Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.76,0:00:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,孤国春秋：七王必死
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.40,0:01:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（根据伯纳德康威尔原着小说改编）
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.08,0:01:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一百年来，这片土地动荡不安\N{\rEn}For a hundred years, there was chaos in our lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.20,0:02:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,萨克逊人和丹麦入侵者掀起战争\N{\rEn}War between Saxons and Dane invaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.36,0:02:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,觊觎王位者大动干戈\N{\rEn}And war between men who wanted to be kings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.52,0:02:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我追随的乌特雷德大人 乌特雷德之子 由丹麦人养大的萨克逊人\N{\rEn}My lord, Uhtred, son of Uhtred, born a Saxon, but raised a Dane,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,则带来了片刻的安宁\N{\rEn}had brought about a fragile peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.84,0:02:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着爱德华国王健康恶化\N{\rEn}But as King Edward's health faltered,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.64,0:02:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动乱接踵而来\N{\rEn}trouble spread.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.36,0:02:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管多数王国向萨克逊人宣誓效忠\N{\rEn}And while most of the country was sworn to the Saxons,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.00,0:02:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德的诺桑比亚却拒绝称臣\N{\rEn}Uhtred's land of Northumbria was not.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.56,0:02:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这也成了敌人亟欲利用的弱点\N{\rEn}And enemies were keen to exploit this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.72,0:02:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（德文特河）
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.60,0:03:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（西诺桑比亚，德文特河）
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.92,0:03:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狼战士！\N{\rEn}Wolf!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.28,0:03:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狼战士！\N{\rEn}Wolf! [grunts] Wolf!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.28,0:03:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把这里毁了，别让人发现我们上岸\N{\rEn}Destroy the settlement. Leave no sign we have landed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.40,0:03:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安拉夫，间谍来了\N{\rEn}Anlaf, we have the spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.44,0:03:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的孩子啊\N{\rEn}Behold my child.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.64,0:03:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安拉夫之女\N{\rEn}Behold the daughter of Anlaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.40,0:03:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像个小丑\N{\rEn}You look ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.52,0:03:53.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是他们的装扮，父亲\N{\rEn}It is how they dress, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.64,0:03:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要混入人群就得…\N{\rEn}If I'm to hide amongst them, I must appear--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.92,0:03:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱德华国王死了吗？\N{\rEn}Is King Edward dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.68,0:03:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还没\N{\rEn}Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.80,0:04:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-但快了 -那我们来对了\N{\rEn}-But each breath could be his last. -Then we chose our moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.52,0:04:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国王驾崩后，萨克逊人必然会起内哄\N{\rEn}A king dies, Saxons always turn on each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.16,0:04:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去通知所有不满他们的国王\N{\rEn}Pass this news to all kings who hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.52,0:04:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说我已从爱尔兰前来，正在寻求结盟\N{\rEn}Tell them I have crossed from Irland and wish to make allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.12,0:04:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你回温彻斯特吧\N{\rEn}Return yourself to Winchester.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.96,0:04:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等待时机\N{\rEn}Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.12,0:04:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好好玩弄他们\N{\rEn}Play with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.80,0:04:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,制造混乱\N{\rEn}Unleash chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.44,0:04:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（温彻斯特）
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.96,0:04:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（威塞克斯王国，温彻斯特）
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.16,0:04:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别动，退后\N{\rEn}No. Stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.32,0:04:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找出王后！\N{\rEn}Find the queen!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.24,0:04:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾格芙王后\N{\rEn}Lady Eadgifu,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.76,0:04:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叛徒艾弗维尔 派人来保护你和艾德蒙王子\N{\rEn}the traitor Aelfweard has sent men to take you and Prince Edmund into protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.40,0:05:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我拒绝成为人质\N{\rEn}I have no wish to be a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.08,0:05:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-能击退他们吗？ -除非有艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}-Can we fight them? -Not without Aethelstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.44,0:05:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,守卫一定能…\N{\rEn}Well, surely, my guards can--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.84,0:05:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人们开始选边站了\N{\rEn}Loyalties are shifting and factions forming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.44,0:05:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不知道谁能信任\N{\rEn}It is not certain who supports us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.12,0:05:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,应该趁早带着王子去避难\N{\rEn}We should flee with your son whilst we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.68,0:05:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这简直无法饶恕\N{\rEn}I will not forgive this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.28,0:05:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不会原谅艾索斯坦 让我们陷入险境\N{\rEn}Nor forgive Aethelstan for leaving us exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.56,0:05:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,竟然抛下我们\N{\rEn}Damn him for his absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.68,0:05:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧，艾德蒙，我们要走了\N{\rEn}Come, Edmund. We are leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.72,0:05:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,王后呢？动作快！搜！\N{\rEn}- Where's the queen? - Move! Look everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.76,0:05:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-母后，这是… -别说话\N{\rEn}- Mother, what's-- - Sh. Quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.96,0:05:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等等\N{\rEn}-Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.60,0:05:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,皮尔里各\N{\rEn}- Pyrlig. - We got word.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.60,0:05:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦为了祈求父亲平安 踏上朝圣之旅了\N{\rEn}Aethelstan has gone on pilgrimage to pray for his father's health.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.92,0:05:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去找他，告诉他国王死了 然后帮我赏他一巴掌\N{\rEn}Then find him and tell him of his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.12,0:05:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他发誓要保护我们的\N{\rEn}Then strike him, from me, for he swore to protect us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧，没时间了\N{\rEn}Come. There's no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.20,0:05:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们要去找谁？\N{\rEn}Where will you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.92,0:06:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-乌特雷德 -投靠异教徒？\N{\rEn}-To Uhtred. -The pagan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.76,0:06:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他们在里面 -快走\N{\rEn}- They're in here! - Go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.08,0:06:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德背叛了我丈夫\N{\rEn}Uhtred betrayed my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.00,0:06:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样妥吗？\N{\rEn}Are we sure this is wise?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.32,0:06:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德视艾索斯坦如己出 绝对可靠\N{\rEn}Uhtred was like a father to Aethelstan. He can be trusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.44,0:06:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要去最后的王国\N{\rEn}We go to the last kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.60,0:06:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（贝班堡）
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.64,0:06:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（诺桑比亚王国，贝班堡）
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.96,0:06:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在军队前大喊：“放箭！”\N{\rEn}He stood in front of the army, and he said, "Release the arrows!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.64,0:06:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,结果一支箭射穿了他的头\N{\rEn}And an arrow went right through his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.52,0:06:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的太精采了\N{\rEn}Oh, that was something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.16,0:06:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片土地上的战役将流传千古\N{\rEn}But then, the battle for this place certainly sticks in the memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.52,0:06:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-两场都是 -对，肯努特\N{\rEn}-Both times. - Hey. Cnut.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.08,0:06:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是个好老二\N{\rEn}He was a proper… cock!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.76,0:06:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有凶猛的屠马人\N{\rEn}Then there were the horse-killers. Oh, they were deadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.92,0:06:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他叫什么？ -血发\N{\rEn}-What was his name? -Bloodhair.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.52,0:07:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,血发，女巫又叫什么？\N{\rEn}Bloodhair. And what was her name? She of the curses?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.68,0:07:02.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别提了，她叫丝凯德\N{\rEn}Do not remind me. Skade!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.88,0:07:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她是疯婆娘\N{\rEn}Now, she was moon touched.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.32,0:07:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另一位先知的下场不太好喔\N{\rEn}Another one who thought she was a seer. It didn't go well for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.96,0:07:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那真的是预知梦，我梦到三次了\N{\rEn}I am telling you, my dream was a prophecy. Three nights I have had it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.24,0:07:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你梦到什么，英格丽丝？ -别问了，大人\N{\rEn}-And what is your dream, Ingrith? - Don't get her started, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.96,0:07:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听好了，“七王丧钟”\N{\rEn}-Hear my words. "Seven kings must die." - Lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.60,0:07:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-七位国王和… -英格丽丝\N{\rEn}-Seven kings and-- -Ingrith!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.76,0:07:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,注意，王后来了\N{\rEn}All stand for the queen!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.32,0:07:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾格芙王后\N{\rEn}Queen Eadgifu.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.44,0:07:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有我最尊贵的朋友，艾德汉大人\N{\rEn}And my most noble friend, Lord Aldhelm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.96,0:07:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么风把你们吹来了？\N{\rEn}What brings you this far north?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.76,0:07:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们母子来寻求庇护\N{\rEn}I come seeking refuge with my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.44,0:07:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱德华国王驾崩了\N{\rEn}Edward, rightful king of these lands, has died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.28,0:08:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很遗憾\N{\rEn}Then my heart grieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.56,0:08:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直想要和解\N{\rEn}I'd hoped to reconcile.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.16,0:08:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个挂了，还剩六个\N{\rEn}One down, six to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.76,0:08:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,够了，我不喜欢这样\N{\rEn}No! I do not like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.00,0:08:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,诺桑比亚将承认艾索斯坦为新王\N{\rEn}Northumbria recognizes the new king, Aethelstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.08,0:08:21.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦不一定能即位\N{\rEn}Do not assume Aethelstan will be king.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.36,0:08:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有谁拥护艾弗维尔？ -威塞克斯诸位郡长\N{\rEn}-Who is supporting Aelfweard? - The ealdormen of Wessex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不意外，还在说艾索斯坦是私生子？\N{\rEn}Of course. Still claiming Aethelstan's a bastard?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.00,0:08:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对，威尔特郡为艾弗维尔提供金援\N{\rEn}Yes. Aelfweard has the wealth of Wiltunscir behind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.64,0:08:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在艾尔斯伯里的间谍 通报他正在当地公开招兵买马\N{\rEn}Our spies in Aegelesburg say he's there, openly recruiting mercenaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.76,0:08:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要在他壮大前 去艾尔斯伯里逮住他\N{\rEn}We will go to Aegelesburg and seize him before he is at full force.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.08,0:08:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们希望你采取防守姿态\N{\rEn}We would prefer your guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.28,0:08:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的提议能争取时间 让艾索斯坦去温彻斯特加冕为王\N{\rEn}My offer gives Aethelstan the time to go to Winchester to be crowned,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.96,0:08:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还能避免军事冲突\N{\rEn}and we avoid a clash of armies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.48,0:08:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我立誓要守护艾索斯坦…\N{\rEn}I swore an oath to protect Aethelstan--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.36,0:08:52.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对，你是信守诺言的人\N{\rEn}And of course, you are a man of your word.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.92,0:08:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你没有履行向国王称臣的承诺\N{\rEn}Yet your oath to swear your lands to the king remains unfulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.44,0:09:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的丈夫对丹麦后裔充满敌意\N{\rEn}Your husband showed himself hostile to those of Danish blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.52,0:09:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不是统一英格兰的最佳人选\N{\rEn}As such, he was not the right man to unite England.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.84,0:09:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否则英格兰早就统一了\N{\rEn}If he had been, England would be united.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.32,0:09:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在不一样了\N{\rEn}But now things can be different.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.32,0:09:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦可以是 实现萨克逊人梦想的国王\N{\rEn}Aethelstan can be the king to fulfill the Saxon dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.12,0:09:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除非他发誓…\N{\rEn}If he chooses to swear--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.56,0:09:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已宣誓效忠，我的誓言依旧有效\N{\rEn}I swore an oath of loyalty, and it stands.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.68,0:09:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果艾弗维尔在招募佣兵 一定会到处放话\N{\rEn}If Aelfweard is buying mercenaries, he will be looking for men from all parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.24,0:09:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样还能发动突袭吗？\N{\rEn}Do you think we can still execute an ambush?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.20,0:09:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果是为了艾索斯坦，当然没问题\N{\rEn}If it is for Aethelstan, then yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.72,0:09:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-只要他不睡着 -就那么一次\N{\rEn}-If he does not fall asleep. -Once. I fell asleep once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.44,0:09:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,确定不派年轻战士吗？\N{\rEn}Are you certain this is better than a band of young fighters?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.00,0:09:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听说你们最近都在饮酒作乐\N{\rEn}I hear you do little these days but feast and hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.24,0:09:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会把自己发的誓 丢给年轻人去实现\N{\rEn}I will not send young men to do a task I swore to do myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.20,0:10:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧，臭家伙…\N{\rEn}Come on, you little…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.32,0:10:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快啊\N{\rEn}Come on! Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.68,0:10:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在停下来。\N{\rEn}Stop it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.32,0:10:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥斯柏，边境怎么样？ 苏格兰人没作乱吧？\N{\rEn}Osbert! What news from our borders? Do the Scots behave themselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.04,0:10:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,父亲，听说德文特河畔有狼战士\N{\rEn}Yes, Father. There are rumors Wolf-Warriors landed near Derwent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.08,0:10:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-狼战士？ -你背着剑做什么？\N{\rEn}-Wolf-Warriors? -Why are you carrying your sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.72,0:10:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要去保护艾索斯坦 不受他弟弟伤害\N{\rEn}We're riding to protect Aethelstan from his brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.32,0:10:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也去\N{\rEn}Then I will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.32,0:10:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我要与你并肩作战留下来 - 守着你应得的领土吧\N{\rEn}-Any fight of yours is mine. -Stay here and protect your birthright.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.32,0:10:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被动等待准没好事\N{\rEn}No good comes of sitting waiting for a birthright.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.68,0:10:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你就训练马匹\N{\rEn}So you train the horses
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.12,0:10:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,教教那男孩怎么保护自己\N{\rEn}and you teach that boy how to defend himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.96,0:10:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先王的三儿子不怎么讨喜\N{\rEn}No one likes the third son of a dead king.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.24,0:10:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,父亲\N{\rEn}Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.76,0:10:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你会向艾索斯坦称臣吗？ -我必须遵守诺言\N{\rEn}-Will you swear our lands to Aethelstan? -I must honor my word.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.44,0:10:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,诺桑比亚人一定会很舍不得 他们的异教领主\N{\rEn}Northumbrians will be sad to lose their pagan lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.56,0:10:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,终于出来了\N{\rEn}Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.52,0:10:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个小王八蛋\N{\rEn}-Look at this little bastard. -Are we ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.00,0:10:54.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-准备好了吗？ -他在抱怨他的马鞍\N{\rEn}He's complaining about his saddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.00,0:10:57.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-说害他屁股痛 -不是屁股，是背\N{\rEn}-Says his arse gets sore. - Didn't say arse. I said my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.80,0:10:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我帮你做了这个\N{\rEn}I made you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.12,0:11:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们每个人都有\N{\rEn}And one for each of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.32,0:11:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐在冷冰冰的地上 迟早变成冷冰冰的尸体\N{\rEn}Men who sit on cold earth find the cold earth calls for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.76,0:11:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她再次证明了自己的预知能力\N{\rEn}Once again, she shows herself a seer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.36,0:11:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人，你别当真\N{\rEn}Lord, it was nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.92,0:11:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再说一次吧\N{\rEn}Tell it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“七王丧钟”，大人\N{\rEn}"Seven kings must die," Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.64,0:11:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-“七位国王…” -别说了\N{\rEn}-"Seven kings--" -Ingrith, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.08,0:11:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,继续说\N{\rEn}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.04,0:11:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“和你心爱的女人”\N{\rEn}"And the woman you love."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.04,0:11:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我并非国王，也没有女人\N{\rEn}I'm no king, and I have no woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.64,0:11:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-对我毫无意义 -乌特雷德大人\N{\rEn}-It means nothing. - Lord Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.60,0:11:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已吩咐儿子训练王子\N{\rEn}I told my son to train yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.04,0:11:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瓦莎可以服侍你\N{\rEn}While you are here, take Wassa as your serving woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.64,0:11:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-当自己家 -关于艾索斯坦，我想说一件事\N{\rEn}-Make this fortress your home. -I wish to say one thing of Aethelstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.24,0:11:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已经不像从前那般无忧无虑\N{\rEn}He is not quite the carefree boy you raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.32,0:11:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他现在非常虔诚\N{\rEn}He has grown very much into his faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.80,0:12:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥斯华兄弟会对他影响极深\N{\rEn}The Brotherhood of Oswald exert great influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.00,0:12:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我吓跑不少这种人，修士都莫名怕我\N{\rEn}I have scared off such men before. For some reason, monks find me terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.24,0:12:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我们再次拥立新王吧\N{\rEn}- Let's go play kingmaker. - Once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.36,0:12:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（格拉斯顿伯里）
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.56,0:12:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（威塞克斯王国，格拉斯顿伯里）
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.48,0:12:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,父王去世了？不可能\N{\rEn}My father? No, that cannot be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.52,0:12:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝说他会活过冬天的\N{\rEn}I thought God had given him the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦大人 你得赶快到威塞克斯加冕\N{\rEn}Lord Aethelstan, you should make haste to Wessex for coronation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.20,0:12:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你弟弟正在召集人手\N{\rEn}Your brother gathers men.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.24,0:12:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,务必趁他结成大军前 返回温彻斯特登基为王\N{\rEn}Establish yourself at Winchester before he raises an army.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.24,0:13:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会遵从上帝的命令 皮尔里各神父\N{\rEn}We will leave when God commands us to leave, Father Pyrlig.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.64,0:13:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝尚未要求我们离去\N{\rEn}And that command has not been given.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.84,0:13:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祷告完就回去吧\N{\rEn}Return when you have prayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.48,0:13:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我该离开吗？\N{\rEn}Do I depart?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.24,0:13:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有圣经知道\N{\rEn}Only the book has answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.28,0:13:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧\N{\rEn}Play.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你被指引至《马太福音》第57节\N{\rEn}You have been guided to the Book of Matthew, verse 157.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.36,0:14:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“于是耶稣动身前往推罗与西顿海岸”\N{\rEn}"Then Jesus went thence and departed into the coasts of Tyre and Sidon."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.08,0:14:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝要你战斗\N{\rEn}God wants you to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.08,0:14:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（艾尔斯伯里）
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.88,0:14:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（麦西亚王国，艾尔斯伯里）
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.92,0:14:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是谢了\N{\rEn}Oh. Thank you, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.64,0:14:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,停，有何贵干？\N{\rEn}Halt. State your business here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.12,0:14:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们听说有人在招募战士\N{\rEn}We heard a man is looking for fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.12,0:14:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想来赚点钱\N{\rEn}We come to make some coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.32,0:14:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进去吧\N{\rEn}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.96,0:14:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这里简直成了地狱 -爱德华任它凋零\N{\rEn}-This place has fallen to shit. - Edward left it to decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.68,0:14:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幸好艾塞弗蕾德不必见证这一切\N{\rEn}I'm glad Aethelflaed is not here to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.88,0:15:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都接到消息了\N{\rEn}Word has spread.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.92,0:15:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我敢说一半的人都是熟面孔\N{\rEn}I swear I've fought half these men.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.16,0:15:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这不是普通的招兵买马 -是要开战了\N{\rEn}This is not someone trying to recruit. This is preparing for a battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.36,0:15:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个年轻人就是艾弗维尔\N{\rEn}That is the youth Aelfweard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.44,0:15:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去探听他的计划\N{\rEn}Go see what men know of his plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.68,0:15:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我给你看一把剑!\N{\rEn}I'll show you a sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.36,0:15:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你剑上那个是琥珀？ -怎么卖？\N{\rEn}-Is that amber in your sword? -How much do you want for it?\N{\rEn}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.72,0:15:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-回去喝奶吧  -艾格，冷静\N{\rEn}- Go home to your mothers. - Edgar! No.\N{\rEn}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.68,0:15:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,威佛！\N{\rEn}Wilfrid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.20,0:15:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,威佛！\N{\rEn}Wilfrid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.44,0:15:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你叫我？\N{\rEn}Do you speak to me, friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.84,0:16:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉，我以为你是威佛\N{\rEn}Your pardon. I thought you were Wilfrid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.96,0:16:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们曾在泰腾豪之战并肩作战\N{\rEn}A great man I fought with at Tettenhall.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.60,0:16:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你打过泰腾豪之战？\N{\rEn}Wait, you were at Tettenhall?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.44,0:16:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我父亲也有参战\N{\rEn}My father was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.04,0:16:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你现在为谁效命？ -艾弗…什么的\N{\rEn}-Who do you fight for now? -Aelf… something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.68,0:16:17.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-萨克逊人名字都很像 -要出征威塞克斯的艾弗维尔？\N{\rEn}-Saxon names are much alike. -The Aelf who marches on Wessex?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.00,0:16:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看来你们没听说\N{\rEn}You haven't heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.64,0:16:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不打算攻打威塞克斯\N{\rEn}No one's marching on Wessex.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.28,0:16:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在的计划是把艾索斯坦引过来\N{\rEn}I'm told the new plan is to lure Aethelstan here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.24,0:16:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦要来了\N{\rEn}Aethelstan is on his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.12,0:16:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他接下艾弗维尔发的战帖\N{\rEn}Aelfweard challenged him to battle, and he's accepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.44,0:16:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他为什么要迎战？\N{\rEn}Why would he agree to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.24,0:16:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还年轻，中了圈套\N{\rEn}Because he's young, and they've baited him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.04,0:16:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们派人埋伏在山丘 打算在城门逮他\N{\rEn}They plan to snare him between the gate and men hidden in the hills.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.68,0:16:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要在他抵达前拿下控制权\N{\rEn}Then we take control before he arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.96,0:16:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人，光靠我们拿不下这座城镇\N{\rEn}We can't seize this town with just us, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.80,0:16:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有那个必要\N{\rEn}We do not need to seize the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.40,0:17:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,兄弟，要不要小赌一下？\N{\rEn}Hey! Can I tempt you to play for money, friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.84,0:17:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把他们绑起来、门锁好 艾索斯坦抵达前不要轻举妄动\N{\rEn}Tie them up and secure the bolt. Stay low until Aethelstan arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.44,0:17:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果有床就归我\N{\rEn}If there's a bed, it's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.16,0:18:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他来了\N{\rEn}He's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.56,0:18:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发出警报！大军接近南门！\N{\rEn}Raise the alarm! Soldiers approach the southern gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.16,0:18:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,站住，艾尔斯伯里现在效忠于我\N{\rEn}Come no further! Aegelesburg is loyal to me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.08,0:18:36.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不跟私生子谈判\N{\rEn}We do not negotiate with bastards.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.36,0:18:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也拒绝投降\N{\rEn}Nor do we surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.00,0:18:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你只能饿死我们 -弟弟，我不是傻子\N{\rEn}-You'll have to starve us out. -I am not foolish, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.72,0:18:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我早预料你会设下陷阱\N{\rEn}I assumed you would place a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.08,0:18:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把我牵制在此，再从后方包夹\N{\rEn}Perhaps delay me here until your forces could attack at rearguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.12,0:18:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把埋伏的人带上来\N{\rEn}Show him what's left of his men!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.24,0:19:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,立刻投降\N{\rEn}You can yield now,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.08,0:19:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否则我们破门而入，血洗这里\N{\rEn}or we destroy the gate and kill all your men.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.28,0:19:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,城门牢不可破 我绝不投降\N{\rEn}The gates will hold. No yield will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.88,0:19:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你就跟城门一起下地狱吧\N{\rEn}Then you will be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.84,0:19:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,准备开门\N{\rEn}Get ready to open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.24,0:19:10.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我才是合法的王位继承人 你母亲是婊子\N{\rEn}I am the rightful king. Your mother was a whore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.96,0:19:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有良知的人都明白，而且你没有盟友\N{\rEn}All good men know it. You have no allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.60,0:19:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾弗维尔大人\N{\rEn}Lord Aelfweard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.40,0:19:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我是贝班堡的乌特雷德 -乌特雷德\N{\rEn}-I'm Uhtred of Bebbanburg. -Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.56,0:19:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我向来直言不讳\N{\rEn}You know me as a man who speaks the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.92,0:19:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相信我，为了所有人好，放弃吧\N{\rEn}so hear me when I say, for the common good, stand down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.88,0:19:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的人控制了城门，你是以寡敌众\N{\rEn}My men control the gate. You're outnumbered on all sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.60,0:19:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投降吧\N{\rEn}Yield.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.28,0:19:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让这一切和平落幕\N{\rEn}Let this end with peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.52,0:19:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投降吧，弟弟\N{\rEn}Give yourself to me, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.28,0:19:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会追究的\N{\rEn}Then it is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.72,0:20:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请原谅我的无能\N{\rEn}Forgive me for my failings,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.36,0:20:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请安慰我母亲的族人\N{\rEn}and give comfort to my mother's kin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.60,0:20:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉他们我已被流放\N{\rEn}Tell them of my exile
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.04,0:20:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及我们曾为了光宗耀祖而奋斗\N{\rEn}and how we sought to honor our discarded bloodline.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.88,0:20:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-为威塞克斯而战！\N{\rEn}-For Wessex! - For Wessex!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.96,0:20:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德大人\N{\rEn}Lord Uhtred,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.60,0:20:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打开城门\N{\rEn}open the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.84,0:20:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不！ -我是上帝选择的合法继承人\N{\rEn}-No! - God chose me rightful heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.08,0:20:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦！\N{\rEn}Aethelstan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.64,0:21:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上\N{\rEn}Advance!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.08,0:21:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杀个片甲不留\N{\rEn}Leave no enemy alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.92,0:21:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人，快阻止这场闹剧\N{\rEn}Lord, stop this madness!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.08,0:21:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,住手！\N{\rEn}Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.36,0:21:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦！\N{\rEn}Aethelstan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.68,0:21:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,退后，躲起来\N{\rEn}Get back! Hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.20,0:21:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我投降，拜托不要…\N{\rEn}- I submit! Please don't--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.96,0:21:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}Aethelstan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.76,0:21:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,求求你，饶了我吧\N{\rEn}Please, show mercy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.08,0:22:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不！\N{\rEn}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.40,0:22:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,住手！他们已经投降了！\N{\rEn}Stop! They're surrendering!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.20,0:22:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦！\N{\rEn}Aethelstan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.56,0:22:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦！\N{\rEn}-Aethelsta--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.04,0:22:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人，救救我们\N{\rEn}Lord! Lord, help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.40,0:22:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦！\N{\rEn}Aethelstan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.68,0:23:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}Aethelstan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.16,0:23:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-叫你的人住手 -乌特雷德，你来做什么？\N{\rEn}-Stand down your men. - Uhtred, why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.56,0:23:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来阻止战争，敌人已经投降了\N{\rEn}To stop this. Your enemy has surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.56,0:23:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叫你的人住手\N{\rEn}Halt your men.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.48,0:23:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-让他过来，去叫停 -是，大人\N{\rEn}-Let him approach and call a halt. - Yes, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.48,0:23:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你怎么了？ -你才怎么了？\N{\rEn}-What happened to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.96,0:23:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-没必要杀了你弟 -当然有必要\N{\rEn}-You had no need to kill your brother. -I did, or in time, he would return.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.12,0:23:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他迟早会卷土重来 -你没有遵守诺言\N{\rEn}-You dishonored your word. -I did not.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.96,0:23:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我叫他投降，没说要留他活口\N{\rEn}I told him to yield. I did not say he would survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.52,0:23:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们本来就不打算让他活命 大人，请撤回命令\N{\rEn}It was never our plan to let him live. Lord, reverse the order.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.88,0:23:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们即将击溃敌人\N{\rEn}We are close to routing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.40,0:23:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-那些佣兵跟你无冤无仇 -你不找他帮忙是对的\N{\rEn}-Hired men have no quarrel with you. -You were right not to seek his help.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.00,0:23:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杀了一百个父亲 就会有三百个儿子反抗你\N{\rEn}You kill 100 fathers, you give 300 sons a reason to defy you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.48,0:23:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动动脑啊！\N{\rEn}Think!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.20,0:23:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在正是统一的时候\N{\rEn}Now's the time to unify.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.32,0:23:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德说得有道理\N{\rEn}Uhtred may be right in this matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.60,0:24:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是以过来人的身分提出劝告\N{\rEn}I speak only as a man who has made mistakes before.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.60,0:24:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我是贝班堡的… -我知道你是谁\N{\rEn}-I'm Uhtred of-- -I know who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.32,0:24:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德，这位是英格曼德大人\N{\rEn}Uhtred, this is Lord Ingilmundr.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.12,0:24:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是了不起的指挥官 也是我的好朋友\N{\rEn}A great commander and a great friend to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.96,0:24:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那他也是我的朋友了\N{\rEn}Then a friend to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.20,0:24:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么会有丹麦人的名字？\N{\rEn}Why the Danish name?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.08,0:24:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是萨克逊人养大的丹麦人\N{\rEn}Born to a Dane, but raised a Saxon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.24,0:24:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾佛雷德的写作使我皈依基督教\N{\rEn}I found Christ through the works of Alfred,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.20,0:24:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在罗马的儿子也透过文字启发了我\N{\rEn}and indeed through the writings of your son in Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.76,0:24:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你一定以他为傲\N{\rEn}You must be proud of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.84,0:24:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是货真价实的学者\N{\rEn}He is a true scholar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.28,0:24:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是赋予他生命的粗人\N{\rEn}I'm just the fool who made him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.32,0:24:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格曼德掌管了 威勒尔半岛塞沃尔的驻军\N{\rEn}Ingilmundr holds the garrison at Thelwael on the Wirral.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.84,0:24:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他认识许多我们在朗可法的旧识\N{\rEn}He knows many of the people we knew from Rumcofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.40,0:24:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们都是好人，希望还能见面\N{\rEn}Good people. I should like to see them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.48,0:24:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好，先向新王宣誓诺桑比亚的忠诚吧\N{\rEn}Yes. Perhaps after you've sworn Northumbria to the new king.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.00,0:24:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,遵守你的诺言\N{\rEn}Honor your word.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.52,0:24:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把你欠他父亲的还回来\N{\rEn}Swear to Aethelstan what you denied his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.16,0:24:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,交出你的土地 让英格兰成为完整的国家\N{\rEn}Cede your lands and make England whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.52,0:24:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像你说的\N{\rEn}As you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.48,0:24:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是时候统一了\N{\rEn}it is the time for unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.16,0:25:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会向国王效忠，但你尚未登基\N{\rEn}I will swear to a king, and you are not yet crowned.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.24,0:25:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我拒绝以这副血淋淋的模样立誓\N{\rEn}Nor will I kneel to you covered in blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.72,0:25:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会在温彻斯特的大厅宣布放弃领地\N{\rEn}I will renounce my lands in the Great Hall at Winchester.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.44,0:25:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们不需要繁文缛节 -乌特雷德是信守承诺的人\N{\rEn}-It doesn't need to be done with ceremony. -But Uhtred is a man of his word.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.72,0:25:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来温彻斯特找我\N{\rEn}Come to Winchester.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.24,0:25:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把伤口治好\N{\rEn}Heal the wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.32,0:25:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他怎么知道我们要来？\N{\rEn}How did he know we were coming here?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.48,0:25:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他总是有办法保护我\N{\rEn}He's always found a way to protect me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.44,0:25:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许他派人盯着你\N{\rEn}Perhaps he has friends who keep one eye on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.20,0:25:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我母亲也这样\N{\rEn}My mother was the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.12,0:25:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真窝心，你还听他的话\N{\rEn}It's touching, how you still defer to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.48,0:25:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他一直都忠心耿耿 -你太高尚了，竟然相信他\N{\rEn}-He's been steadfast a long time. -And noble that you trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.80,0:25:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他可是背叛了你父亲\N{\rEn}Given all that went on with your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.24,0:25:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（史特灵）
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.28,0:25:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（苏格兰王国，史特灵）
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.20,0:26:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪个王子赢了？\N{\rEn}Which boy prevailed?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.08,0:26:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}Aethelstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.76,0:26:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他冷血地杀了自己的手足 即将登基为萨克逊王\N{\rEn}Killed his brother in cold blood and will now claim the Saxon crown.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.28,0:26:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看来大势已定 有和平条约的消息吗？\N{\rEn}Then it's settled. Any word on renewal of the treaty?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.64,0:26:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去催促温彻斯特\N{\rEn}Push Winchester.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.04,0:26:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-动用你的关系 -陛下，还有一件事\N{\rEn}-Make contact. -Lord, we've had word of something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.80,0:26:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-丹麦人安拉夫想要谈谈 -那个食人族？\N{\rEn}-The Dane, Anlaf, seeks a meeting. -The one who eats the flesh of men?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.36,0:26:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还找了曼岛、昔得兰 和奥克尼的国王\N{\rEn}An assembly with you, and the kings of Man, Shetland, and Orkney.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.80,0:26:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一个基督徒 才不会傻呼呼去见一群丹麦国王\N{\rEn}I will not be the lone Christian lured to meet Dane kings.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.96,0:26:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们也许有不错的提议\N{\rEn}They might offer something of interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.32,0:26:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去跟萨克逊人谈和平条约\N{\rEn}Seek to renew a peace with Saxons.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.04,0:26:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱德华维持了停战协议 他儿子没理由打破\N{\rEn}Edward kept the truce. We have no reason to think his son will not.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.68,0:26:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会去传话\N{\rEn}I'll send word.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.68,0:26:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他亲手杀了自己的兄弟\N{\rEn}His own flesh, put to the knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.08,0:27:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他比你说的还要残忍 -他变冷酷了\N{\rEn}-He is more brutal than you suggested. -His heart has hardened.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.16,0:27:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,反对他的人会更不满\N{\rEn}Which should harden those against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.56,0:27:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不列颠诸王都接到消息了吗？ -他们当耳边风\N{\rEn}-Do other kings in Britain hear our call? -They pretend to be deaf to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.48,0:27:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-其实都听进去了 -是该如此\N{\rEn}-But I know they listen. -They should.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.16,0:27:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦将变得贪婪\N{\rEn}Aethelstan will become greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.00,0:27:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对野心再了解不过，父亲\N{\rEn}You would know ambition, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.48,0:27:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等你继承了我的土地，你也会明白的\N{\rEn}Eh, and when my lands are yours, you will know it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.60,0:27:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回去温彻斯特\N{\rEn}Return to Winchester.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.00,0:27:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盯紧每一个人\N{\rEn}Watch everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.48,0:27:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有消息随时回报\N{\rEn}And bring me word when there's word to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.68,0:27:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-父亲，你受伤了？ -小伤\N{\rEn}- Father, have you been injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.00,0:27:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托告诉我这不是真的\N{\rEn}-Nothing that will not heal. - Tell me the news is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.60,0:27:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦杀了他的手足？\N{\rEn}-Did Aethelstan turn on his own blood? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.44,0:27:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对，艾弗维尔死了 艾德蒙千万不能回到温彻斯特\N{\rEn}-Aelfweard did not survive. -Then Edmund cannot return to Winchester.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.12,0:27:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他将永远被视为威胁\N{\rEn}He will always be seen as a rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.80,0:27:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦向来疼爱你儿子\N{\rEn}Aethelstan has always shown great affection for your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.16,0:27:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她说得对\N{\rEn}But she is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.48,0:27:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他受人影响了\N{\rEn}He has fallen under an influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.04,0:28:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会在贝班堡待到情势安全为止\N{\rEn}I shall not leave Bebbanburg until the threat passes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.48,0:28:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这里永远欢迎你 -情势会好转的\N{\rEn}-You're welcome here as long as you wish. - And it will pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.24,0:28:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国王的职责将导正艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}The duties of kingship will focus Aethelstan's mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.68,0:28:10.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我该回南方了\N{\rEn}But I should return south.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.88,0:28:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会确认他的状态\N{\rEn}I will assess the mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.32,0:28:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Hallelujah ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.88,0:28:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,♪ Hallelujah ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.80,0:28:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全能永生的上帝\N{\rEn}Almighty and everlasting God,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.80,0:28:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请以恩典与祝福洗净祢的仆人\N{\rEn}pour out the spirit of thy grace and blessing upon this, thy servant,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.56,0:28:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦国王\N{\rEn}King Aethelstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.76,0:28:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们于今日举行按手礼，加冕他为王\N{\rEn}That, as by the imposition of our hands, he is this day crowned king.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.60,0:28:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蒙上帝圣宠\N{\rEn}So he may, by thy sanctification,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.92,0:28:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他将透过基督，我们的主 继续做祢拣选的仆人，直到永远\N{\rEn}continue always thy chosen servant, through Christ, our Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.00,0:28:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请赐予他亚伯拉罕的信念\N{\rEn}Grant him the faith of Abraham,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.48,0:28:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所罗门的智慧\N{\rEn}the wisdom of Solomon,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.56,0:29:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及大卫的勇气\N{\rEn}the courage of David.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.04,0:29:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivat Rex!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.04,0:29:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivat Rex!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.64,0:29:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivat Rex!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.44,0:29:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（二：威塞克斯、麦西亚 与东英格兰国王）
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.96,0:29:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivat Rex!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.64,0:29:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivat Rex!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.80,0:29:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivat Rex!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.40,0:29:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没来观礼\N{\rEn}You were not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.04,0:29:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们盼望已久的一刻\N{\rEn}This moment was all we had talked of.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.08,0:29:35.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你却缺席了 -对\N{\rEn}-And you were not there. -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.24,0:29:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在这里\N{\rEn}I was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.52,0:29:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,圣经的召唤至高无上\N{\rEn}The call of the scripture always comes first.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.64,0:29:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也同意吧？\N{\rEn}You believe that, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.36,0:29:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然了\N{\rEn}Yes, yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.64,0:29:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你将成为伟大的英格兰国王\N{\rEn}Then you will be a great king of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.48,0:29:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会像艾佛雷德一样受人赞颂\N{\rEn}And all will speak of you as they did Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.08,0:30:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德履行承诺了吗？\N{\rEn}Does Uhtred stand by his word?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.36,0:30:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，乌特雷德没来\N{\rEn}No. Uhtred has not come.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.92,0:30:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他显然认为… -他想继续在自己的领土称王\N{\rEn}-Clearly, he-- -He wishes to remain king in his own land.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.64,0:30:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,愿上帝保佑他不受虚荣蒙蔽\N{\rEn}May God protect him from his vanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.20,0:30:19.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对你而言，这是残酷的事实\N{\rEn}But towards you, it is a cruelty.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.88,0:30:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我感到非常遗憾，来\N{\rEn}And I am sorry. Here. Come. Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.08,0:30:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他竟然折磨你善良的灵魂\N{\rEn}What torture to enact on so kind a soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.80,0:30:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我以为你们都遗弃我了 -我绝不会那么做\N{\rEn}-I thought you had both abandoned me. -Of course I would not.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.00,0:30:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我很讶异乌特雷德竟如此愚蠢\N{\rEn}I'm just surprised Uhtred could be so foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.16,0:30:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为岁月能使他增长智慧\N{\rEn}You would've thought his years would make him wiser.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.20,0:30:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许在他眼中，你依旧是个孩子\N{\rEn}Perhaps he still sees the boy you once were,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.44,0:30:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不是顶天立地的男子汉\N{\rEn}and not the man you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.72,0:31:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人\N{\rEn}Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.56,0:31:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然比不上蛇息剑…\N{\rEn}It's not Serpent's Breath, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.68,0:31:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这把更轻盈、更锋利 镶有石榴石\N{\rEn}it's lighter, it's sharper, and it's got a garnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.28,0:31:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,取个名字吧\N{\rEn}Give it a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.48,0:31:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,斩魂剑\N{\rEn}Manslayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.36,0:31:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绝后剑\N{\rEn}Ball-taker.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.20,0:31:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德，乌特雷德之剑\N{\rEn}Uhtred, Sword of Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.80,0:31:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你笑了，大人\N{\rEn}You actually smiled, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.88,0:32:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许失去蛇息剑是个预兆 代表我该退出战场了\N{\rEn}Perhaps losing my sword was a sign that my battle days are over.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.56,0:32:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这时候挑衅国王可不妙\N{\rEn}A bad time to provoke the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.44,0:32:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没有挑衅他\N{\rEn}I did not provoke him.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.88,0:32:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是给他时间证明自己不是暴君\N{\rEn}I'm simply giving him time to prove he's not a tyrant.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.24,0:32:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-否则… -怎么样？\N{\rEn}-Otherwise… -Otherwise what?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.60,0:32:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“七王丧钟”，原因是什么？\N{\rEn}"Seven kings must die." For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.84,0:32:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你妻子看到了什么？ -什么都没有\N{\rEn}-What did your wife see? -She sees nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.44,0:32:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我发誓\N{\rEn}I swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.72,0:32:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们在庆祝什么？\N{\rEn}What do they celebrate?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.00,0:32:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,驯马成功\N{\rEn}The breaking of the horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.88,0:32:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感谢奥斯柏如此照顾艾德蒙\N{\rEn}Thank Osbert for the care he has shown Edmund.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.00,0:32:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是贝班堡的一分子了\N{\rEn}He's part of Bebbanburg now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.28,0:32:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们都是\N{\rEn}You both are.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.92,0:33:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对，我儿子变了许多\N{\rEn}Yes, my son is quite changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.32,0:33:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在宫里的忧郁一扫而空\N{\rEn}There was a somberness at the palace that has lifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.96,0:33:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为这里空气清新\N{\rEn}It's the air here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.04,0:33:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,使人神清气爽\N{\rEn}Brings out good spirits in everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.52,0:33:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyah!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.72,0:33:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你似乎更开朗了\N{\rEn}You yourself seem happier.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.16,0:33:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错，乌特雷德大人\N{\rEn}I am, Lord Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.00,0:33:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经放下悲痛，而且…\N{\rEn}Some grief has passed, and I feel…
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.56,0:33:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更有信心面对世界了\N{\rEn}more ready for the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.56,0:33:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,控制马匹，很好\N{\rEn}Control! Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.84,0:33:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,主啊，请怜悯我们的灵魂 宽恕我们的罪恶\N{\rEn}Forgive us these sins that we commit.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.28,0:33:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们能得到宽恕吗？\N{\rEn}Will we be forgiven?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.00,0:33:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们罪孽深重\N{\rEn}Our sin weighs heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.32,0:33:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对\N{\rEn}Yes, it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.08,0:33:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但别忘了\N{\rEn}But remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.40,0:34:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝会进行审判\N{\rEn}God holds us in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.40,0:34:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,信仰能抵销一切罪过\N{\rEn}Every sin can be weighed against an act of faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.68,0:34:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,增加信仰，就能减少罪过\N{\rEn}Grow the faith and the sin is diminished.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.00,0:34:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果罪孽深重到无法饶恕呢？\N{\rEn}What if the shadow of sin obscures the faith?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.72,0:34:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟我来\N{\rEn}Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.68,0:34:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许你该实现祖父对英格兰的梦想\N{\rEn}Perhaps return to your grandfather's vision for England.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.44,0:34:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许让异教徒皈依基督教 才是当务之急\N{\rEn}Perhaps now there is an urgency to bring the pagans to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.12,0:34:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那样会…\N{\rEn}Will that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.12,0:34:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洗净我吗？\N{\rEn}cleanse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.92,0:34:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你和我？\N{\rEn}Us?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.84,0:34:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然，福音传得越远，信仰就越强\N{\rEn}Well, surely the greater the lands, the greater the faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.32,0:34:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把艾佛雷德的梦想发扬光大\N{\rEn}Go beyond what Alfred dreamed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.12,0:34:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放眼上帝创造的土地 而非人类划分的领土\N{\rEn}Look to the islands God made, not the countries ordained by men,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.32,0:34:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,引领所有人成为祂的子民\N{\rEn}and bring all to Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.60,0:34:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你接受审判时\N{\rEn}So when you are judged,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.88,0:34:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就能得到赦免\N{\rEn}you will be found in balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.24,0:35:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大方拥抱罪过…\N{\rEn}And thus may accept both the sin…
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.96,0:35:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勇敢出征吧\N{\rEn}and the conquest against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.44,0:35:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（诺桑比亚南方边境）
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.92,0:35:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人\N{\rEn}Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.88,0:35:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别说了\N{\rEn}Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.80,0:35:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们在聊什么？\N{\rEn}What do you talk of?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.16,0:35:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊，夫人，请恕我无礼\N{\rEn}Oh my faith, Lady. I cannot lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.72,0:35:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的妇女都很关心乌特雷德大人 希望他能找个女伴\N{\rEn}The ladies here care for Lord Uhtred and wish keenly he would find a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.60,0:35:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那她们要失望了\N{\rEn}Well, they shall be sore of heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.24,0:36:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先王遗孀不会嫁给领主的\N{\rEn}The widow of a king will not marry a lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.60,0:36:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我应该多加注意言行举止\N{\rEn}I shall have to be more careful in how I conduct myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.20,0:36:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夫人，八卦还不是最可怕的\N{\rEn}It is not the gossips you should fear, Lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.76,0:36:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和平的日子可能不会长久\N{\rEn}This peace may not sustain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.24,0:36:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德大人怠慢了国王\N{\rEn}Lord Uhtred has snubbed the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.68,0:36:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德心爱的女性 都会成为敌人的目标\N{\rEn}The women Uhtred has affection for become a target for his enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.00,0:36:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希崔里克\N{\rEn}- Sihtric! -Sh-sh.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.52,0:36:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有什么消息？\N{\rEn}What have you learnt?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.68,0:36:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦占领了埃弗维治\N{\rEn}Aethelstan has claimed Eoferwic.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.36,0:36:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说朗弗德死了，没有国王 所以领土归他\N{\rEn}He says since Rognvaldr is dead, there is no king, so it belongs to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.80,0:36:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,埃弗维治？\N{\rEn}Eoferwic?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.24,0:36:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们现在认我为领主 艾索斯坦知道的\N{\rEn}They see me as their lord now. Aethelstan knows this.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.24,0:36:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要求所有人进贡\N{\rEn}He is demanding all come with tribute.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.56,0:36:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不只是萨克逊首领，是全不列颠国王\N{\rEn}Not just Saxon chiefs, but all kings of Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.76,0:36:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,包括整片大陆和所有海岛\N{\rEn}All the mainland and all the outlying islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.20,0:36:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人\N{\rEn}Lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.20,0:37:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这里称王吧\N{\rEn}Declare yourself king here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.32,0:37:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像你祖先那样\N{\rEn}Like your forebears.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.16,0:37:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，他可是艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}No. This is Aethelstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.60,0:37:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他误入歧途，我就必须点醒他\N{\rEn}If he chooses the wrong path, I must tell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.88,0:37:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人\N{\rEn}Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.00,0:37:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（埃弗维治）
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.08,0:37:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（诺桑比亚王国，约克）
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.80,0:37:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“根据新法令，全境皆须纳税”\N{\rEn}"There went out a decree that all the world should be taxed."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.64,0:37:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不必进贡，通通回村子去\N{\rEn}You owe no tribute! Return to your villages.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.28,0:37:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-乌特雷德，冷静点 -皮尔里各，进贡是怎么回事？\N{\rEn}-Uhtred! Calm yourself. -Pyrlig? What is this tribute?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.40,0:37:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说是为了建教堂 小声点，到处都是间谍\N{\rEn}He says it is to build churches, but, please, there are spies everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.44,0:37:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉你家的兔崽子他太小看苏格兰了\N{\rEn}Tell your arseling apprentice he's badly misjudged the mood of Scotland.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.64,0:37:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么生气\N{\rEn}You seem upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.84,0:38:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们来谈和平条约\N{\rEn}We came to renew our treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.48,0:38:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却被晾了好几天，还被说是来乞讨的\N{\rEn}Instead, we've been left waiting for days, only to be told we are supplicants.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.12,0:38:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,劝你们小心点\N{\rEn}I would be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.20,0:38:15.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人来找我们结盟\N{\rEn}We've had other offers of alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.48,0:38:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦为何这么做？ 他说是为了团结基督徒\N{\rEn}-Why is Aethelstan doing this? -He says to unite Christians.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.72,0:38:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在祷告中不断提到赎罪\N{\rEn}And in his prayers, he talks much of atonement.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.12,0:38:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赎罪？什么罪？\N{\rEn}Atonement? For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.16,0:38:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他弟弟的死？他的私生子身分？\N{\rEn}The death of his brother, the bastardy of his parentage?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.20,0:38:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不清楚\N{\rEn}I do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.64,0:38:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和艾德汉大人天天在劝他\N{\rEn}Lord Aldhelm and I try daily to dissuade,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.04,0:38:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他满口征服天下、强迫洗礼\N{\rEn}but there is talk of conquest and forced baptism.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.40,0:38:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他在哪里？ -恶魔石\N{\rEn}-Where is he? -The Devil's Stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.64,0:38:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他认为自己能战胜恶魔\N{\rEn}He thinks he fights the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.16,0:38:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这简直胡来，艾德汉\N{\rEn}This is madness. Aldhelm.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.28,0:39:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些石头已经耸立好几个世代了\N{\rEn}These stones have stood for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.56,0:39:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显然对上帝不敬\N{\rEn}They are an insult to God, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.68,0:39:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是斯特拉斯克莱德国王欧文吗？\N{\rEn}Is that Owain, King of Strathclyde?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.76,0:39:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦要他亲眼见证\N{\rEn}Aethelstan wanted him to witness it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.60,0:39:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些是他祖先的杰作\N{\rEn}They were built by his forebears.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.84,0:39:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他想要羞辱权贵？\N{\rEn}He is seeking to humiliate powerful men?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.88,0:39:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海威尔国王\N{\rEn}King Hywel.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.84,0:39:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（四：威尔斯国王）
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.84,0:39:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他竟然要威尔斯称臣？\N{\rEn}He dares ask submission from Wealas?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.60,0:39:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们对麦西亚有功\N{\rEn}After all you did for Mercia?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.24,0:39:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德，我能怎么办？\N{\rEn}What choice do I have, Uhtred?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.80,0:39:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他把我儿子抓去温彻斯特\N{\rEn}He took my son to Winchester.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.48,0:39:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他把你儿子当人质？\N{\rEn}He is keeping your son hostage?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.96,0:39:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抓走儿子，等于抓走未来的国王\N{\rEn}You take the son, you take a future king.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.12,0:39:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我只能听从他的命令 -我会告诉他这种事不可原谅\N{\rEn}-Now I am forced to follow his bidding. -I will tell him this cannot stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.32,0:39:47.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海威尔国王 我保证威尔斯的忠诚不会被践踏\N{\rEn}King Hywel, I swear, Wealas's faithfulness will not be spat on.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.52,0:39:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的诗人曾说过\N{\rEn}Our poets spoke this.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.68,0:39:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,萨克逊人将为了打造自己的国家 而摧毁我们\N{\rEn}That a Saxon would break us all to build their country.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.88,0:39:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不只是萨克逊人的国家\N{\rEn}This is not just a Saxon country.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.44,0:40:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾德汉，带我去见他 我要阻止这一切\N{\rEn}Aldhelm, get me close to him. I will stop this.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.52,0:40:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,站住，退后\N{\rEn}Halt. Stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.92,0:40:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让开，国王要召见乌特雷德\N{\rEn}Step aside! The king requested Uhtred speak with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.00,0:40:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦国王\N{\rEn}King Aethelstan!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.28,0:40:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,陛下\N{\rEn}Lord King,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.36,0:40:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想跟你私下谈谈\N{\rEn}let me speak with you alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.12,0:40:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你不该侵占我的领土 -你也不该违背誓言\N{\rEn}You should not have stepped on my land.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.12,0:40:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你当年羞辱父王\N{\rEn}You should not have broken your word, humiliated me,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.60,0:40:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在又羞辱我\N{\rEn}as you humiliated my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.24,0:40:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是要点醒你，你误入歧途了\N{\rEn}I'm trying to make you see you're on the wrong path.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.96,0:40:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你对英格曼德唯命是从 -我只听从上帝\N{\rEn}-You do the bidding of Ingilmundr-- -I do the bidding of the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.60,0:40:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你打算强迫丹麦人改变信仰？\N{\rEn}Do you really seek to convert Danes?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.44,0:41:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我没教你尊重两个字吗？ -很多丹麦人欢迎上帝\N{\rEn}-Did I teach you nothing of respect? -Many Danes welcome the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.52,0:41:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-宫里的人都很感激 -也有人不想改变信仰，你心知肚明\N{\rEn}-Those in my court thank me for it. -Many do not wish it, and you know this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.60,0:41:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦，你明明知道的\N{\rEn}Aethelstan, you've always known it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.12,0:41:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-连艾佛雷德都尊重这一点 -我要赎的罪更多\N{\rEn}-Even Alfred respected this. -I have more to atone for than Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.80,0:41:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁说的？英格曼德？\N{\rEn}Who tells you this? Ingilmundr?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.72,0:41:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是不是说你不能没有他的指引？\N{\rEn}Does he tell you you are damned without his guidance?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.56,0:41:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看过太多人被神棍耍得团团转了\N{\rEn}For I've seen before men under the spell of those who claim to know the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.88,0:41:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是我忠实的朋友\N{\rEn}He has been a great friend to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.44,0:41:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦，你爱睡谁都行\N{\rEn}Aethelstan, hump who you wish,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.04,0:41:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但千万别被觊觎权力的人…\N{\rEn}but do not fall under the influence of those who seek power--
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.92,0:41:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是谁放出这种恶毒的指控？\N{\rEn}Who makes such vicious claim against me?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.04,0:41:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-没人 -是谁在撒谎？\N{\rEn}-No one. -Who tells such lies?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.64,0:41:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-没有任何传闻 -艾德汉大人是间谍吗？\N{\rEn}-It has not been talked of. -Lord Aldhelm, does he spy for…
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.48,0:41:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是谁传了什么？传多久了？\N{\rEn}What has been said, by who, and for how long?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.72,0:41:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有任何传闻 我也不在乎，我只在乎你\N{\rEn}No one has said anything. I care not for that, but for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.24,0:41:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦，你很善良，但心肠太软\N{\rEn}Aethelstan, you are a kind man, but you are tenderhearted,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.56,0:41:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格曼德在为自己和兄弟会谋权\N{\rEn}and Ingilmundr is seeking power for himself and for his brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.24,0:41:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是说谎、诽谤\N{\rEn}Lies. Lies and ignominy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.72,0:41:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没有诽谤，他让你背弃家人\N{\rEn}There's no ignominy. He just turns you from your kin.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.16,0:41:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你才背弃了你的国王！\N{\rEn}And you are turned from your king!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.76,0:41:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你打算自己称王\N{\rEn}You seek to be one yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.84,0:42:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,陛下，现在要为土地祝圣\N{\rEn}Lord, they consecrate the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.84,0:42:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请你赐予祝福\N{\rEn}and would request you to give the blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.88,0:42:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没问题\N{\rEn}Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.76,0:42:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让诺桑比亚国王反省一下自己的错误\N{\rEn}Let us leave the King of Northumbria to think on his errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.48,0:42:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对王位没兴趣\N{\rEn}I have no dream to be a king.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.84,0:42:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只想保护你\N{\rEn}Only to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.00,0:42:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你上次去艾尔斯伯里保护他 不是被年轻人毒打一顿？\N{\rEn}Like you ran to protect him in Aegelesburg and ended up being beaten by boys?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.48,0:42:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,剑都被小鬼头抢走了 还有资格说话吗？\N{\rEn}Should he really take counsel from a man who loses his sword to a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.32,0:42:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,诺桑比亚需要骁勇善战的领主\N{\rEn}Northumbria needs a lord with lust for battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.80,0:42:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,据说安拉夫已上岸 他将大肆烧杀掳掠\N{\rEn}There are rumors Anlaf has arrived and will come Viking.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.64,0:42:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别以为你们有同样的信仰 他就会饶你一命\N{\rEn}Do not think he will spare you just because you follow the same gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.40,0:42:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,留他一晚，逼他在日出宣誓效忠\N{\rEn}Keep him here a night and make him swear at dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.24,0:42:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你迟早会来乞求他的帮忙\N{\rEn}In time, you will come begging for his help.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.68,0:42:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,父亲都会倒下\N{\rEn}As all fathers fall,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.36,0:43:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,由儿子取而代之\N{\rEn}and all sons take their place.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.08,0:43:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格曼德大人宣布你是上帝的敌人\N{\rEn}Lord Ingilmundr has declared you an enemy of God
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.16,0:43:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还煽动追随者杀了你\N{\rEn}to incite his followers to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.00,0:43:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦不会允许这种事\N{\rEn}Aethelstan would not allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.80,0:43:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以英格曼德才要装作没有涉入其中\N{\rEn}Which is why Ingilmundr seeks to keep his hands clean of it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.00,0:43:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已经离开了\N{\rEn}and has left the camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.20,0:43:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去哪里？\N{\rEn}To go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.60,0:43:43.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这边\N{\rEn}This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.32,0:43:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上去吧，没有守卫\N{\rEn}Go up and around. There's no guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.36,0:44:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是他\N{\rEn}Him. That is the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.00,0:44:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你跟异教徒说了什么？\N{\rEn}What did you speak of with the pagan?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.84,0:44:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有骑兵接近\N{\rEn}Horsemen approach!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.68,0:44:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,停，报上名来\N{\rEn}Stay back from my gates and tell me who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.76,0:44:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是英格曼德大人 应乌特雷德大人的要求前来\N{\rEn}Lord Ingilmundr, and I come at Lord Uhtred's request.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.08,0:44:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要重新向国王宣誓效忠 在埃弗维治耽搁了\N{\rEn}He's delayed in Eoferwic as he renews his vow to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.84,0:44:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以请我来保护你\N{\rEn}He asked I help protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.44,0:44:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保护我？\N{\rEn}Protect from what?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.84,0:44:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,据说狼战士在德文特河畔上岸了\N{\rEn}There is a rumor of Wolf-Warriors landed near Derwent.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.56,0:44:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打开城门\N{\rEn}Open the gate! Open the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.00,0:44:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要这么做\N{\rEn}Do not give the order.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.72,0:45:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们曾经同甘共苦\N{\rEn}Think on all we have shared.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.84,0:45:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你迷失自我了，艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}You're lost from yourself, Aethelstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.52,0:45:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们一起对抗…\N{\rEn}We fought together--
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.56,0:45:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你放话中伤我，还跟乌特雷德密谋\N{\rEn}And despite this, you drip poison against me and plot with Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.08,0:45:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不是的 -是\N{\rEn}-No. -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.04,0:45:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不是 -是\N{\rEn}-No. -Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.36,0:45:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你背叛了我，艾德汉\N{\rEn}You turned your back, Aldhelm.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.64,0:45:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只好回敬你\N{\rEn}Now I turn mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.40,0:46:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格曼德大人\N{\rEn}Lord Ingilmundr,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.24,0:46:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是好消息 乌特雷德大人要称臣了\N{\rEn}you bring welcome news of Lord Uhtred's supplication.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.00,0:46:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你愿意伴我南下，让我亲眼见证吗？\N{\rEn}Will you journey south with me to let me bear witness to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.08,0:46:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夫人，大伙都骑累了 至少让我们休息一天吧\N{\rEn}Lady, we have ridden hard to get here. At least let us rest a day or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.12,0:46:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是我被困在贝班堡好久了\N{\rEn}Oh, but I have been trapped in Bebbanburg a good while.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.76,0:46:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相信我，此地不宜久留\N{\rEn}Believe me, you do not want to find yourself here longer than intended.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.16,0:46:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他们接到警告了！ -上！\N{\rEn}-They've been warned! - Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.24,0:46:56.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们抢先赶到了\N{\rEn}We overtook you on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.60,0:47:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你对艾索斯坦的控制就到此为止了\N{\rEn}Whatever power you hold over Aethelstan,\N{\rEn}today it ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.40,0:47:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的剑\N{\rEn}My sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.56,0:47:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还想上英灵殿\N{\rEn}You still believe in Valhalla!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.40,0:47:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦很在乎你，我可不要他怨我\N{\rEn}Aethelstan cares for you. I will not divide us further.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.76,0:47:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把他关在下面\N{\rEn}Put him below.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.92,0:47:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,基督徒，快来救我！ 你们的主人是谁？\N{\rEn}Christians amongst you, defend me! Who is your Lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.40,0:47:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德大人还是耶稣基督？\N{\rEn}Lord Uhtred or the Lord Jesus Christ?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.12,0:47:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贝班堡人民不会为了信仰而分裂\N{\rEn}The people of Bebbanburg will not be divided by faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.84,0:47:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蠢蛋，起来抗争！\N{\rEn}Rise up, you fools!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.32,0:47:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去通知国王释放条件\N{\rEn}Tell the king the terms of his release.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.72,0:47:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要和诺桑比亚达成和平协定 确立边境\N{\rEn}He makes peace with Northumbria and guarantees the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.88,0:47:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不得强迫任何人改变信仰 -是的，大人\N{\rEn}-No one is forced to follow his god. -Yes, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.68,0:47:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,条件真多\N{\rEn}Quite a price.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.20,0:47:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-艾索斯坦会同意吗？ -希望如此\N{\rEn}-Will Aethelstan agree? - Let us hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.72,0:47:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他现在抛弃朋友速度挺快的\N{\rEn}He seems to discard his friends rather quickly now.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.04,0:48:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你祝福了卑微的灵魂\N{\rEn}Truly, you bless an unworthy soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.44,0:48:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-愿上帝赏赐你的仁慈 -阿门\N{\rEn}-May God reward your kindness. -Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.60,0:48:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（曼岛）
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.84,0:48:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（曼岛）
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.44,0:48:41.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（诸王集会）
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.48,0:48:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（五：奥克尼国王）
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.40,0:48:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（六：昔得兰国王）
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.08,0:48:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦背弃了朋友\N{\rEn}Aethelstan turns against his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.04,0:48:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妄想成为全天下的帝王\N{\rEn}Succumbs to a wild dream to be a monarch for all your land.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.20,0:49:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他迟早会去找你，昔得兰国王\N{\rEn}In time, he will come for you, Shetland.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.68,0:49:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有你，奥克尼国王\N{\rEn}You, Orkney.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.92,0:49:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他会夺走你祖先的领土 称之为不列颠\N{\rEn}He will take what belonged to your forebears and call it Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.60,0:49:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不可能\N{\rEn}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.52,0:49:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个萨克逊乡巴佬鲜少出航\N{\rEn}He barely sets his foot upon the water. Saxon country folk.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.04,0:49:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以赶跑他们\N{\rEn}We can repel them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.32,0:49:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的提议不只如此\N{\rEn}我提议征服回去\N{\rEn}I'm not talking of repelling, but of meeting conquest with conquest.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.28,0:49:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,苏格兰不加入\N{\rEn}Scotland rejects your offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.84,0:49:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不跟异教徒 联手攻打毫无威胁的人\N{\rEn}We cannot join with pagans to attack a man who's not threatened us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.68,0:49:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,基督徒不会选择战争\N{\rEn}Christians do not choose war.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.08,0:49:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,战争即将爆发\N{\rEn}War is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.04,0:49:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你只能选边站\N{\rEn}You only have to choose a side.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.64,0:50:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,愿上帝与你同在\N{\rEn}God be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.28,0:50:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,石头滚开了，就像圣经那样\N{\rEn}The stone was rolled away, as in the scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.56,0:50:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一定是天使显灵\N{\rEn}It can only be the work of an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.20,0:50:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这边，大人，快来看看宝物\N{\rEn}This way, Lord. Come and see the treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.52,0:50:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人\N{\rEn}Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.72,0:50:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他怎么说？\N{\rEn}What word from Eoferwic?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.24,0:50:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他接受条件吗？\N{\rEn}Does he accept my terms?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.52,0:50:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没有消息回报\N{\rEn}I have no news.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.04,0:50:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦回温彻斯特了\N{\rEn}Aethelstan is said to have returned to Winchester.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.92,0:50:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,姑且当成好兆头吧\N{\rEn}Well, let us take it as a good sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.00,0:50:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,少了他的影响 艾索斯坦应该能清醒点\N{\rEn}Perhaps without his shadow, Aethelstan sees more clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.48,0:50:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们来这里做什么？\N{\rEn}What trouble brings you out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.20,0:50:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,村民找到异教徒的银子\N{\rEn}The villagers were hunting for pagan silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.40,0:50:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们宣称是奇蹟\N{\rEn}Now they're saying it's a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.28,0:51:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让诺桑比亚国王通过\N{\rEn}Make way for the King of Northumbria.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.32,0:51:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就说吧\N{\rEn}I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.28,0:51:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们都把你当国王\N{\rEn}They think of you as a king.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.04,0:51:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会不会想分一半？\N{\rEn}Do you think they hope to keep half for themselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.00,0:51:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说不定是他们从贝班堡拿来的\N{\rEn}They likely took it from Bebbanburg in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.44,0:51:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要以艾索斯坦国王的名义拘捕你\N{\rEn}You are detained in the name of King Aethelstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.32,0:51:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人\N{\rEn}Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.20,0:51:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是圈套\N{\rEn}We've been lured here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.28,0:51:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也觉得？\N{\rEn}You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.76,0:51:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人，对不起\N{\rEn}Lord, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.48,0:51:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉，大人\N{\rEn}I'm sorry, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.48,0:51:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俘虏说我必须这么做 否则会受地狱之火吞噬\N{\rEn}The prisoner told me I had to, or I'd burn in the fires of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.64,0:52:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我死都不会下令打开城门\N{\rEn}I will never order to open the gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.32,0:52:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,确定？\N{\rEn}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.52,0:52:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是国王送的礼物\N{\rEn}A gift from the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.28,0:52:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦杀了他？\N{\rEn}Aethelstan did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.56,0:52:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是叛徒的下场\N{\rEn}It's what he does to traitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.92,0:52:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打开城门，否则我杀了你父亲\N{\rEn}Open the gates or I slaughter your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.64,0:52:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乖乖配合我就饶他一命\N{\rEn}Comply and he will be spared.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.20,0:52:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要开\N{\rEn}Do not open.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.88,0:52:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我会当你的面杀了他 -不要开！\N{\rEn}-I can kill him in front of you. -Do not open!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.08,0:52:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你决定吧 -奥斯柏，不要开门！\N{\rEn}-The choice is yours. - Osbert! Do not open!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.08,0:52:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,父亲，既然你不在，这里由我做主\N{\rEn}In your absence, Father, I command here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.00,0:52:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我下令开城门 -不要啊！\N{\rEn}And I command that we open.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.12,0:52:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不！\N{\rEn}-No! - No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.48,0:52:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放下武器\N{\rEn}Drop your sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.76,0:52:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前进\N{\rEn}Move.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.68,0:52:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不可以\N{\rEn}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.00,0:52:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦呢？\N{\rEn}Where is Aethelstan?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.76,0:53:01.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别急\N{\rEn}In time.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.24,0:53:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把艾格芙夫人带过来\N{\rEn}Bring me the Lady Eadgifu.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.40,0:53:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过来\N{\rEn}Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.84,0:53:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我自己会走\N{\rEn}I can walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.08,0:53:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动手吧\N{\rEn}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.24,0:53:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杀了我\N{\rEn}Kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.16,0:53:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要把你送到圣岛的修道院\N{\rEn}You are to be placed in the community on Lindisfarne
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.72,0:53:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保护你的贞洁\N{\rEn}to protect your virtue.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.52,0:53:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你跟异教徒睡了吗，夫人？\N{\rEn}Did you hump the heathen, Lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.88,0:53:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,承认吧\N{\rEn}Confess.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.92,0:53:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我承认\N{\rEn}I confess
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.88,0:53:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我向上帝祈祷你早日惨死\N{\rEn}to have prayed for your excruciating death.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.76,0:53:38.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有吗？太可惜了\N{\rEn}A no, then. You should have tried when you had the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.84,0:53:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你儿子将加入我在塞沃尔的驻军\N{\rEn}We're taking your son to my garrison
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.44,0:53:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-接受战斗训练\N{\rEn}at Thelwael where he will be trained for battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.68,0:53:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不，请饶了他\N{\rEn}No. No. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.92,0:53:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-动起来 -还有你儿子\N{\rEn}- Move! -Your son also.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.64,0:53:48.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不，艾德蒙是艾佛雷德的血脉\N{\rEn}No. Edmund is the blood of Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.76,0:53:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不是盾墙的料\N{\rEn}He should not be fodder for a shield wall! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.00,0:53:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我求你了 -我会照顾他\N{\rEn}- I will take care of him. -Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.76,0:53:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德之子将为威塞克斯而战\N{\rEn}The son of Uhtred stands for Wessex.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.44,0:54:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冷静\N{\rEn}Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.76,0:54:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们对你另有打算\N{\rEn}You, we have a plan for.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.96,0:54:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他打算淹死我吗？ -我从来都摸不透他\N{\rEn}- Am I to be drowned in the sea? - I never quite know his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.00,0:54:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别惩罚贝班堡的人 这是我跟他的战争\N{\rEn}Do not punish those in Bebbanburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.84,0:54:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的战场在别处\N{\rEn}-His fight is with me. -His fight is elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.64,0:54:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真走运，苏格兰就这么近\N{\rEn}How lucky we have found ourselves so close to the Scottish border.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.96,0:54:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别入侵苏格兰，你会失去上百名士兵\N{\rEn}No, do not invade Scotland. You will lose hundreds of men.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.68,0:54:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还会引发数个世代的战争\N{\rEn}And unleash a war for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.32,0:54:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国王没有后顾之忧，这也使他更强大\N{\rEn}The king has no successor to fear for. It makes him strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.68,0:54:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想办法保护我们的儿子 别反抗，听他的话\N{\rEn}Do whatever you must to protect our sons. Do not fight him. Just capitulate.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.96,0:54:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要做傻事\N{\rEn}Anything else is foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.04,0:54:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-艾德汉没有背叛你 -你们全背叛了我\N{\rEn}-Aldhelm never betrayed you. -All of you betrayed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.56,0:54:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亏我当你们是朋友\N{\rEn}All those I thought as friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.24,0:54:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在贝班堡前对我称臣，我就饶你一命\N{\rEn}Swear now, before Bebbanburg, and I will spare your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.84,0:54:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我拒绝 -那我只能杀了你\N{\rEn}-No. -Then you leave me with no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.92,0:55:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}Aethelstan.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.32,0:55:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我办不到\N{\rEn}I cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.48,0:55:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我来效劳… -免了\N{\rEn}-Let me offer my-- -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.48,0:55:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把他剥光\N{\rEn}Take everything from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.08,0:55:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你被放逐了，别再踏上我的土地\N{\rEn}I banish you from my lands to travel the earth and seas alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.96,0:55:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否则你儿子将小命不保\N{\rEn}On pain of murder of your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.68,0:55:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁敢给他温饱，就是与我为敌\N{\rEn}Let none feed or clothe him, lest become my enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.08,0:55:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走吧\N{\rEn}Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.28,0:55:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,趁我还没改变心意\N{\rEn}Before this mercy vanishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.76,0:56:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回头吧，现在还来得及\N{\rEn}Turn back. There is still time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.96,0:56:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,苏格兰人不是威胁\N{\rEn}The Scots are no threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.16,0:56:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是造孽啊，陛下\N{\rEn}This will damn you, Lord King.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.92,0:56:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,驱逐异教徒也许是正义之举\N{\rEn}To save us from the pagans can be a just endeavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.60,0:56:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但背叛基督徒是不敬之举\N{\rEn}But to turn on other Christians is ungodly.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.00,0:57:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的手下并不想打这场仗\N{\rEn}Your men do not want this fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.20,0:57:07.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许我需要更好的战士\N{\rEn}Well, perhaps I need better men.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.68,0:57:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许我该把你儿子找来\N{\rEn}Perhaps I should summon your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.80,0:57:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,陛下\N{\rEn}Lord King!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.92,0:57:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦攻打了苏格兰低地的聚落\N{\rEn}Aethelstan has attacked settlements in the lowlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.44,0:57:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须反击\N{\rEn}He cannot raid us without reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.28,0:57:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要不要通知安拉夫 你准备出席诸王集会了？\N{\rEn}Do I tell Anlaf you are ready to meet with him and the other kings?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.04,0:57:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,丹麦屠夫乌特雷德\N{\rEn}Uhtred the Daneslayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.32,0:58:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在本夫利特之役杀了\N{\rEn}You killed my cousin Gelf at the battle of Beamfleot.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.36,0:58:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我堂弟葛夫\N{\rEn}…the battle of Beamfleot.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.20,0:58:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去回报找到他了\N{\rEn}Send word we have found him.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.08,0:58:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我超讨厌葛夫\N{\rEn}I hated Gelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.92,0:58:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,葛夫，葛夫…\N{\rEn}Gelf, Gelf…
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.44,0:58:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带他去见国王\N{\rEn}Take him to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.40,0:58:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们要带我去哪？\N{\rEn}Where are you taking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.80,0:58:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最北端的岛屿\N{\rEn}To the very north of these islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.08,0:58:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（昔得兰）
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.32,0:58:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（昔得兰群岛）
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.32,0:58:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们在庆祝什么？\N{\rEn}What do you give thanks for?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.36,0:58:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,庆祝大战即将开打\N{\rEn}For the great battle to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.04,0:58:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通知首领诺桑比亚国王来了\N{\rEn}Tell the jarl we're here with the King of Northumbria.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.80,0:59:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这里全是昔得兰人？ -也有曼岛人和奥克尼人\N{\rEn}- All folk of Shetland? - Some of Man and Orkney join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.08,0:59:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们的国王也在\N{\rEn}With their kings.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.96,0:59:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是…\N{\rEn}Is this who they claim?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.48,0:59:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,诺桑比亚国王？\N{\rEn}The King of Northumbria?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.88,0:59:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对，没错\N{\rEn}Aye, it's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.20,0:59:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我并非国王 -对\N{\rEn}-I am no king. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.24,0:59:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你有机会称王\N{\rEn}But you could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.68,0:59:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐吧，我们是你的朋友\N{\rEn}Sit. You are amongst friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.52,0:59:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你竟然加入异教徒？\N{\rEn}You join with pagans?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.36,0:59:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦打破了停战协议\N{\rEn}Aethelstan has taken an axe to the truce.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.28,0:59:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你从中调停的协议\N{\rEn}A truce you brokered.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.16,0:59:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他蹂躏了低地村庄…\N{\rEn}What he has done in the villages of the lowlands--
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.60,0:59:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有他在爱尔兰凶残吗？\N{\rEn}-Is it worse than his cruelty in Irland? -Tales to spread fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.84,1:00:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-那是为了散播恐惧的谣言 -我们被迫迎战\N{\rEn}We had no choice but to defend ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.40,1:00:02.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这并非我们所愿\N{\rEn}We did not start this.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.40,1:00:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你们怎么找到我的？间谍是谁？ -我们有很多间谍，掌握了很多情报\N{\rEn}-How did you find me? Who's your spy? -We have many spies. We know many things.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.76,1:00:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道你被艾索斯坦放逐了\N{\rEn}We know Aethelstan has banished you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.08,1:00:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们也知道他喜欢被人骑\N{\rEn}And we know he gets humped like a woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.16,1:00:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许这对你们异教徒没什么\N{\rEn}That may be customary to you pagans,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.96,1:00:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们基督徒绝不容许\N{\rEn}but as a Christian, it cannot be endured.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.00,1:00:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我听说他可享受了 -那么…\N{\rEn}-He endures it often, from what I hear. -So…
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.76,1:00:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,既然你跟我们有共同的敌人\N{\rEn}As a man who shares our enemy,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.44,1:00:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟我们结盟吧，乌特雷德\N{\rEn}we ask you to join with us, Uhtred, in our alliance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.80,1:00:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一起对抗暴君\N{\rEn}Stand against the tyrant.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.88,1:00:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经厌倦战争了\N{\rEn}I'm heartsick of battles.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.52,1:00:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不是战士吗？你不想去英灵殿了？\N{\rEn}What has become of the warrior? Do you no longer yearn for Valhalla?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.20,1:00:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德，你知道预言吗？\N{\rEn}Do you know the prophecy, Uhtred?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.40,1:00:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们族人有个古老预言\N{\rEn}The ancient prophecy of my people?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.20,1:00:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全不列颠将联合起来对抗萨克逊人\N{\rEn}All of Britain will unite against the Saxons,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.52,1:00:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把他们推入肯特海\N{\rEn}push them into the Kentish sea,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.40,1:00:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重新效忠亚瑟王的血脉\N{\rEn}return the feals to the line of Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.24,1:00:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错\N{\rEn}There.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.88,1:00:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,耆老的预言\N{\rEn}The vision of an old man.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.48,1:00:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-绝对不会错 -我们诺桑比亚也有个预言\N{\rEn}-So it must be true. -We Northumbrians also have a prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.72,1:01:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“七王丧钟”\N{\rEn}"Seven kings must die."
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.52,1:01:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没什么好怕的\N{\rEn}That holds no fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.80,1:01:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在场每个人都有继承人\N{\rEn}Each man here has a son to take his place.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.36,1:01:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,七位国王\N{\rEn}Seven kings die,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.00,1:01:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,逝去的同时 也有七位国王崛起\N{\rEn}seven will, in that moment, be made.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.76,1:01:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没错\N{\rEn}It's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.88,1:01:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要有子嗣，王国就能延续到下一代\N{\rEn}If you make a child, your kingdom stands beyond you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.88,1:01:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,饱受战争蹂躏的王国\N{\rEn}A kingdom ravaged by war, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.16,1:01:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有一个可能的\N{\rEn}Then there is another way
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.76,1:01:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,办法\N{\rEn}to consider.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.32,1:01:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果真要避免血战\N{\rEn}If you wish to save many from bloodshed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.24,1:01:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只杀一个人\N{\rEn}Kill one man only.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.20,1:01:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杀了攻打所有人的国王\N{\rEn}Kill the king who has attacked us all.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.60,1:01:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回去请求他的饶恕\N{\rEn}Return to him in… supplication.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.32,1:01:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伺机而动\N{\rEn}Seize the moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.08,1:01:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要夺走一条生命，就能拯救众生\N{\rEn}Save many lives by simply taking one.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.32,1:01:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否则就是开战\N{\rEn}The alternative, of course, is war.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.00,1:01:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,七王对一王\N{\rEn}Seven kings against one.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.24,1:01:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果艾索斯坦想团结不列颠的部落\N{\rEn}If Aethelstan wanted to unite the tribes of Britain,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.04,1:01:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那他已经成功了\N{\rEn}he has succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.24,1:02:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你来做什么？\N{\rEn}Why do you seek us here?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.44,1:02:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的任务是让温彻斯特火力全开\N{\rEn}Your part is to keep Winchester aroused.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.84,1:02:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么放走乌特雷德？\N{\rEn}You let Uhtred go free. Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.76,1:02:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我给了他任务\N{\rEn}I sent him away.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.92,1:02:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去杀死你的国王朋友\N{\rEn}To kill your friend, the king.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.48,1:02:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他会先没命的\N{\rEn}-Well, he will be killed in the attempt.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.16,1:02:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德比你高明多了\N{\rEn}Uhtred has skills you do not.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.44,1:02:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管是他攻击艾索斯坦 还是艾索斯坦攻击他\N{\rEn}He attacks Aethelstan. Aethelstan attacks him.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.20,1:02:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都无所谓\N{\rEn}It barely matters.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.56,1:02:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总之开战时，对手将士气低落\N{\rEn}Either way, we face in battle men whose spirits have been broken.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.08,1:02:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格曼德，你去西边，时候快到了\N{\rEn}Ingilmundr, go to the West. The time is near.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.96,1:02:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亚丝翠，盯紧我们在诺桑比亚的朋友\N{\rEn}Astrid, watch our friends in Northumbria.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.52,1:03:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（温彻斯特）
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.96,1:03:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（威塞克斯王国，温彻斯特）
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.96,1:03:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没想到又见面了\N{\rEn}I did not think I would see you again.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.08,1:03:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,陛下\N{\rEn}Lord King.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.32,1:03:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要为我儿请求你的宽恕\N{\rEn}In the name of my son, I beg forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.80,1:03:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,饶了他吧\N{\rEn}Spare him.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.20,1:03:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我愿向你称臣\N{\rEn}Let me kneel to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.64,1:04:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我会撤除你的放逐令\N{\rEn}Then I lift your banishment.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.88,1:04:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给我一把剑，都出去吧\N{\rEn}Give me a sword and then leave us.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.16,1:04:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧\N{\rEn}Go on, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.84,1:04:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宣誓吧\N{\rEn}Do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.52,1:05:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以吾儿性命发誓\N{\rEn}I swear this on my son's life.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.16,1:05:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,誓词如下\N{\rEn}Hear this as an oath.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.00,1:05:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格曼德是间谍\N{\rEn}Ingilmundr is a spy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.12,1:05:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他和安拉夫联合大不列颠所有国王 打算推翻你\N{\rEn}He's working with Anlaf to ally British kings against you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.08,1:05:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你说谎 -是真的，我在昔得兰见到他\N{\rEn}-Lies. -It is true. I saw him in Shetland.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.40,1:05:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他派安拉夫的战士来找我 企图说服我反叛…\N{\rEn}He told Anlaf's warriors to track me. They tried to turn me--
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.32,1:05:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不可能！\N{\rEn}No!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.88,1:05:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他跟你儿子在塞沃尔！ -他泄露了你的事情\N{\rEn}-He is in Thelwael with your son! -He told them things of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.56,1:05:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还是信奉众神\N{\rEn}He still follows my gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.12,1:05:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你暂时还有优势\N{\rEn}For now, you have an advantage.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.96,1:05:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格曼德不知道自己曝光了\N{\rEn}Ingilmundr does not know he has been discovered.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.88,1:05:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不可能背叛我\N{\rEn}No, he would not betray me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.12,1:05:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我才背叛了他\N{\rEn}If anything, I have betrayed him.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.80,1:05:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不 -他是上帝的信徒，而我是罪人！\N{\rEn}-No. -He is a man of God, and I am a sinner!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.48,1:06:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是他灌输你的，为了让你发起战争\N{\rEn}He has convinced you of this to provoke your campaign.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.88,1:06:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-为了团结你的敌人 -不可能\N{\rEn}-To unite your enemies. -No!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.72,1:06:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦，醒醒吧 他们已经结成巨大的联盟\N{\rEn}Aethelstan, please see this. This alliance he has gathered is too large.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.84,1:06:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-准备来占领你的土地 -不！你说谎！\N{\rEn}-Your lands will be overrun. -No! You lie!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.28,1:06:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全是谎言！\N{\rEn}This is all lies!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.24,1:06:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦，请你听我说\N{\rEn}Aethelstan, please hear me.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.28,1:06:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我为什么要骗你？\N{\rEn}Why would I lie to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.76,1:06:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-出去 -艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}-Get out. -Aethelstan--
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.40,1:06:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,滚，我不想看到你，守卫！\N{\rEn}Get out. Get from my sight! Guards!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.92,1:06:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把他带走\N{\rEn}-Take him!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.60,1:06:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,王八蛋，给我滚\N{\rEn}You dog! On your way.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.52,1:06:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们搜遍了森林山谷\N{\rEn}We search every forest, every valley.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.40,1:06:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,结果他就在繁华的城市\N{\rEn}And here he is, back in the lap of luxury.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.20,1:06:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听说你需要我们\N{\rEn}We heard you needed us.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.44,1:06:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,众神太眷顾我了 给我这么好的朋友\N{\rEn}Truly the gods smiled at me to give me such friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.00,1:06:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们找间酒馆\N{\rEn}Let's find ourselves an alehouse,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.60,1:06:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好好想个对策\N{\rEn}make a plan.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.00,1:07:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-谁告诉你们我在这里？ -她说你需要我们\N{\rEn}-Who told you I was here? - She said you called for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.60,1:07:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没派人传话吗？\N{\rEn}-Did you not send for us, Lord? -She said you needed us.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.00,1:07:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她说你需要护卫\N{\rEn}And requested a guard.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.12,1:07:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个丹麦女生，艾索斯坦的宫女\N{\rEn}Danish girl, serves in Aethelstan's court.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.68,1:07:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费南，我没有派人传话\N{\rEn}Finan, I sent no word.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.08,1:07:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也没有要你们离开贝班堡\N{\rEn}No command for you to leave Bebbanburg.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.48,1:07:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你们在这看守城门 -是，大人\N{\rEn}- Stay here and guard the gates. - Yes, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.32,1:07:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狼战士\N{\rEn}Wolf-Warriors.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.08,1:07:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是安拉夫干的好事\N{\rEn}This is Anlaf's doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.36,1:08:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格丽丝！\N{\rEn}Ingrith!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.76,1:08:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人，大家都去哪了？\N{\rEn}Lord, where are they all?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.08,1:08:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-艾格芙 -乌特雷德\N{\rEn}- Eadgifu? -Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.20,1:08:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么回事？\N{\rEn}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.12,1:08:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们听说这里遭受攻击，状况惨烈\N{\rEn}When news reached us of the attack and torture here,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.56,1:08:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,院长便派我们来协助伤者\N{\rEn}the abbess sent us to help the injured.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.24,1:08:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是我们无法接近他们\N{\rEn}But we cannot get to the injured.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.60,1:08:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她在哪里？我妻子呢？\N{\rEn}Where… Where is she? Where's my wife?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.88,1:09:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“七王丧钟”，大人\N{\rEn}"Seven kings must die," Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.16,1:09:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“七位国王”\N{\rEn}"Seven kings
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.32,1:09:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“和你心爱的女人”\N{\rEn}and the woman you love."
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.28,1:09:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格丽丝！\N{\rEn}Ingrith!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.08,1:09:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-英格丽丝 -全部都来帮忙\N{\rEn}-No. Ingrith! -Every man is to help move it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.04,1:09:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你，去上面\N{\rEn}You, up above.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.20,1:09:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有人听见吗？ -提防安拉夫的手下\N{\rEn}- Can anyone hear me? - Watch for signs of Anlaf's men.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.96,1:09:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们无能为力，只能安抚他们\N{\rEn}We tried to help, but all we could do was comfort them.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.52,1:09:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德，英格丽丝说 他们威胁还会回来\N{\rEn}Uhtred, Ingrith said they threatened to return.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.04,1:09:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们必须保护自己 -先救出里面的人再说\N{\rEn}-We must secure ourselves. -Not until we rescue those within.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.12,1:09:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们上一次说话是什么时候？\N{\rEn}When did you speak last?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.64,1:09:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大约三天前\N{\rEn}About three days ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.00,1:09:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接住绳子\N{\rEn}- Get the rope up there!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.60,1:09:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加油\N{\rEn}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.08,1:09:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用力拉\N{\rEn}Pull!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.16,1:09:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拉\N{\rEn}Pull!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.32,1:09:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用力拉！\N{\rEn}Pull!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.12,1:09:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出力\N{\rEn}Pull!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.60,1:09:59.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用力拉！\N{\rEn}Now!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.72,1:10:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费南\N{\rEn}Finan.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.56,1:10:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她在哪里？\N{\rEn}Where is…
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.60,1:10:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要啊！\N{\rEn}No!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.88,1:11:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我害死他们的\N{\rEn}I brought this on them.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.88,1:11:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一切都是安拉夫造成的\N{\rEn}What they suffered is on Anlaf's account.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.72,1:11:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能被打败\N{\rEn}You cannot let this break you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.12,1:11:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们已残破不堪\N{\rEn}We are broken.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.48,1:11:40.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们没有盟友，没有希望\N{\rEn}We have no allies. We're lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.72,1:11:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须勇敢保卫诺桑比亚 抵御他们再次入侵\N{\rEn}Then we must find the courage to defend Northumbria from their return.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.56,1:11:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要成功困住他们\N{\rEn}If we endure and keep them at siege,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.80,1:11:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格兰各地就有时间备战\N{\rEn}we will give those in other parts of England time to prepare.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.68,1:11:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的牺牲\N{\rEn}Whatever we suffer
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.16,1:11:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能保护远方的人\N{\rEn}protects those we are apart from.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.68,1:11:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她说得对，大人\N{\rEn}She's right, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.00,1:11:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥斯柏可以渡过爱尔兰海…\N{\rEn}Osbert can cross the Irish Sea, get to--
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.32,1:12:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱尔兰海？\N{\rEn}The Irish Sea?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.32,1:12:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们得快马加鞭 安拉夫想让这里成为众矢之的\N{\rEn}We must find the fastest horses. I think Anlaf is hoping to turn all eyes here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.56,1:12:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要引诱艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}To lure Aethelstan.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.84,1:12:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会在自己的地盘登陆\N{\rEn}But they will land where they have men.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.12,1:12:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格曼德掌管威勒尔的驻军\N{\rEn}Ingilmundr holds a garrison in the Wirral.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.80,1:12:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的儿子也在那里\N{\rEn}With… With our sons.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.36,1:12:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（塞沃尔）
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.60,1:12:51.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（威勒尔半岛）
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.44,1:13:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要出事了\N{\rEn}Something's underway.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.16,1:13:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我准备好了\N{\rEn}I'm ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.56,1:13:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保重\N{\rEn}Take care.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.64,1:13:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快进去\N{\rEn}Get in the cart.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.28,1:13:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们看看脖子上的刀，好好想清楚\N{\rEn}Those of you with swords to your throats face a decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.08,1:13:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一千艘船正驶向这里\N{\rEn}A thousand ships are heading towards these shores.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.36,1:13:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些已经上岸了\N{\rEn}Some have already landed.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.52,1:13:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要不了一周 我们就会占领所有萨克逊市镇\N{\rEn}Within a week, Saxon boroughs will be overrun.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.28,1:13:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加入我们，一起推翻暴君艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}Join us and fight the tyrant Aethelstan,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.56,1:13:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否则就去死吧\N{\rEn}or die.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.44,1:13:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为爱德华国王…\N{\rEn}For King Ed--
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.64,1:14:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-别乱动  -这边走\N{\rEn}- Keep still. - This way!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.24,1:14:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的，先生。我相信是的。\N{\rEn}Yes, sir. I believe so.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.96,1:14:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有看见，但他们走了\N{\rEn}We saw them, but they got away.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.20,1:14:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-在很远的地方 -谢谢\N{\rEn}-There. Far away. -Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.28,1:14:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不客气\N{\rEn}Yes, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.44,1:14:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有塞沃尔的消息，大人\N{\rEn}No word from Thelwael, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.36,1:14:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道全都告诉他们了。\N{\rEn}Told them all I knew.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.96,1:14:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希崔里克\N{\rEn}Sihtric.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.76,1:14:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是\N{\rEn}Lord?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.72,1:14:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们终于要面对失败了吗？\N{\rEn}Do we finally face defeat?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.64,1:14:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我所认识的战将\N{\rEn}All the warrior kings that I've known,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.76,1:14:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,厄柏、肯努特、血发\N{\rEn}Ubba, Cnut, Bloodhair,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.64,1:14:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们最终都失败了，还牵连众多生命\N{\rEn}all have faced defeat in the end and have taken others with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.52,1:14:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人，战争永远不会停\N{\rEn}The fight was always coming, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.96,1:14:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,死得轰轰烈烈才是勇士\N{\rEn}No warrior dies a peaceful death.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.56,1:14:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她早就预见了，“七王丧钟”\N{\rEn}She saw it all. "Seven kings must die."
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.56,1:14:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们还有希望\N{\rEn}We have hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.32,1:15:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你从来没有称王的打算\N{\rEn}In your heart, you never wanted to be a king.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.72,1:15:17.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有打听到我儿子的消息吗？\N{\rEn}Have those fleeing heard anything of my son?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.56,1:15:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在得到确定的消息前\N{\rEn}Then until I know for sure,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.52,1:15:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他都还活着\N{\rEn}he is alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.04,1:15:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果征战顺利 也许安拉夫会满足于麦西亚\N{\rEn}And if conquest is easy, perhaps Anlaf may be satisfied with Mercia.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.72,1:15:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-那里土壤肥… -他不会满足的\N{\rEn}-It is fertile-- - He will not be satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.48,1:15:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们是为了 熄灭英格兰统一的梦想而来\N{\rEn}They come Viking now to extinguish an idea of England.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.00,1:15:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个梦想将团结往日的敌人\N{\rEn}A dream unites a people who once sought to kill each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.48,1:15:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一旦熄灭，我们将重回黑暗时代\N{\rEn}Without it, we go back into an age of darkness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.40,1:15:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们都失去了太多\N{\rEn}We have both lost so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.16,1:16:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我问自己\N{\rEn}But I ask myself…
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.00,1:16:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还活着吗？\N{\rEn}am I alive?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.08,1:16:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能感觉到吗？\N{\rEn}Can you feel it?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.44,1:16:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还活着\N{\rEn}You are alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.24,1:16:19.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也是\N{\rEn}So are you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.84,1:16:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们还有希望\N{\rEn}So we have hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.08,1:16:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾德蒙？\N{\rEn}Edmund?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.68,1:16:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥斯柏？\N{\rEn}Osbert?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.24,1:16:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾德蒙？\N{\rEn}Edmund?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.16,1:17:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来找英格曼德\N{\rEn}I came seeking Ingilmundr.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.96,1:17:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了证明你说谎\N{\rEn}To prove that you had lied to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.72,1:17:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你没骗我\N{\rEn}But you had not.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.96,1:17:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是来找儿子的\N{\rEn}We came to search for our sons.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.16,1:17:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带奥斯柏和艾德蒙出来\N{\rEn}Bring out Osbert and Edmund.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.76,1:18:01.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥斯柏\N{\rEn}Osbert!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.08,1:18:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们躲藏起来，逃过了大屠杀\N{\rEn}They hid themselves and were spared the massacre.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.64,1:18:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,陛下\N{\rEn}Lord King,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.32,1:18:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大恩大德，没齿难忘\N{\rEn}you have my endless gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.28,1:18:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过去这一年，我完全变了个人\N{\rEn}I've not been myself this past year, and truly,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.04,1:18:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的，我...\N{\rEn}truly, I…
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.72,1:18:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在终于付出代价\N{\rEn}I pay for my sins.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.96,1:18:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布鲁南博尔集结了大批联军\N{\rEn}I face a great alliance at Brunanburh.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.36,1:18:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后悔没有意义\N{\rEn}All regret is worthless.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.36,1:18:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好好策划如何迎战吧\N{\rEn}Let us speak only of the fight to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.08,1:18:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-奥斯柏，你听到什么消息？ -他们在高地扎营\N{\rEn}-Osbert, what have you learnt? -They've set up camp on high ground.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.76,1:18:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有六支军队\N{\rEn}And they have six armies.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.08,1:18:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,七支军队将在布鲁南博尔交战\N{\rEn}Then seven armies shall meet at Brunanburh.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.04,1:18:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不要你参战，乌特雷德\N{\rEn}I do not want you to fight for me, Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.12,1:18:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我是支持你的… -我知道\N{\rEn}- Trust I'm on your side-- -I know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.32,1:18:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去逃命吧\N{\rEn}Save yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.88,1:18:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,带你儿子去安全之处\N{\rEn}Take your son to safety.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.52,1:18:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要是我战死沙场，还有人能继位\N{\rEn}If I do not survive the battle, then succession will be secure.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.88,1:18:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你无法独自击退联军\N{\rEn}You cannot fight this alliance alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.52,1:18:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我禁止你参战\N{\rEn}Yet I forbid you from taking part.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.64,1:19:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把带他走，皮尔里各神父 全部都带走\N{\rEn}Take him, Father Pyrlig. Please, take them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.60,1:19:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这一切是我造成的 -让我们效力吧\N{\rEn}-I've dragged you all to this fate. - Let us serve you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.40,1:19:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}Aethelstan…
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.64,1:19:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不是对你的惩罚\N{\rEn}this is not a punishment.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.28,1:19:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想我们都心知肚明\N{\rEn}I think we both know that it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.04,1:19:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是以身殉难\N{\rEn}This is martyrdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.40,1:19:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他以寡击众，必死无疑\N{\rEn}He will not survive so great a number.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.48,1:19:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们才得到赦免\N{\rEn}But we have been reprieved.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.84,1:19:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-上帝要我们前往安全之处 -我不信上帝\N{\rEn}-God is telling us to get to safety. -Your god does not speak to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.48,1:19:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,避开必败之战并非懦弱之举\N{\rEn}It is not cowardly to spurn a battle that cannot be won.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.52,1:19:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是\N{\rEn}It is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.36,1:19:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无论如何，我逃跑是不争的事实\N{\rEn}However this prevails, I will have to know I walked away from danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.28,1:19:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也会有属于你的战争\N{\rEn}Your battles will come
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.84,1:19:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等你当上国王之后\N{\rEn}when you become king.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.52,1:19:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,母后，哪里的国王？\N{\rEn}King of where, Mother?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.40,1:19:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要参战\N{\rEn}-We will fight with the shield wall.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.80,1:19:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不 -奥斯柏\N{\rEn}-No. -Osbert,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.80,1:19:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你准备好了吗？ -就等你这句话\N{\rEn}-are you ready? -I've always been ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.60,1:19:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,皮尔里各 你曾说拯救英格兰是我的天命\N{\rEn}Pyrlig, you once told me that it was my destiny to save England.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.72,1:19:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但不是这个样子\N{\rEn}Hadn't seen it quite like this,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.12,1:19:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,算了，反正我也不信预言\N{\rEn}but then I'm not one for prophecies.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.56,1:19:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你的天命是保护艾德蒙呢？\N{\rEn}What if your destiny is to protect Edmund?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.76,1:20:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许他才能统一英格兰 他才是伟大的国王\N{\rEn}Perhaps he is the one to unite England. He could be the king who was worthy.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.84,1:20:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有国王能统一英格兰\N{\rEn}No king will form England.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.24,1:20:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是我现在看到的\N{\rEn}This is what I see now.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.48,1:20:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾德蒙、爱德华、艾佛雷德 甚至艾索斯坦都不可能\N{\rEn}Not Edmund or Edward or Alfred. Not even Aethelstan.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.60,1:20:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾佛雷德的梦想是团结人民\N{\rEn}Alfred's dream was of a united people.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.76,1:20:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为此我和这群来自各地的人奋斗至今\N{\rEn}And with these men, from all parts, I fought for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.92,1:20:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们的天命不是统一英格兰\N{\rEn}What if our destiny was not to form England,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.32,1:20:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是团结英格兰人民呢？\N{\rEn}but to form the English as one force?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.84,1:20:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁比半个撒克逊人和半个丹麦人 更适合领导四分五裂的人民？我们走\N{\rEn}Who better than a half Saxon, half Dane to lead men from divided places? We go!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.76,1:20:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我应该不必称自己英格兰人吧？\N{\rEn}I don't have to call myself English, do I?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.52,1:20:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（布鲁南博尔）
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.40,1:20:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（威勒尔半岛，布鲁南博尔）
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.80,1:21:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,庆祝成这样，好像已经胜利似的\N{\rEn}To hear that, you'd think they'd won already.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.12,1:21:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们应该前进\N{\rEn}We should make our way.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.44,1:21:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果要赢，就得加入前线\N{\rEn}If this is to work, we need to be on the front line.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.68,1:21:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-攻击敌人的左侧 -为什么？\N{\rEn}-We'll aim for their left side. -Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.16,1:21:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么是左侧？\N{\rEn}Why the left?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.56,1:21:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,较没防备，人们大多用右手挥剑\N{\rEn}Weaker. Most men fight with the sword in their right hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.68,1:22:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟乌特雷德征战多次，相信他吧\N{\rEn}I've fought with Uhtred many times. Trust he will find a way.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.60,1:22:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你\N{\rEn}You.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.72,1:22:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这把剑哪来的？\N{\rEn}Where did you find that?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.20,1:22:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在艾尔斯伯里用五枚硬币买来的\N{\rEn}I bought it in Aegelesburg for five pieces.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.72,1:22:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能借看吗？\N{\rEn}May I?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.96,1:22:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我用这把跟你交换\N{\rEn}I will exchange it for this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.76,1:22:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这更值钱，上面还有石榴石\N{\rEn}It is worth much more, and it has a garnet.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.04,1:22:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别讨价还价 那把剑归你，这把剑归我\N{\rEn}When I say exchange, I mean you take that one, and I keep this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.28,1:22:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是你们的指挥官，也不是将领\N{\rEn}I am no commander of yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.20,1:22:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是身经百战的战士\N{\rEn}I have no authority other than being a man who has fought in many battles.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.04,1:22:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些人曾在我的麾下\N{\rEn}Some of you I have led before.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.96,1:23:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天，我以士兵的身分 与各位并肩作战\N{\rEn}Today I stand with you as a simple soldier.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.32,1:23:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我请求各位 再次在战场上\N{\rEn}But I ask that, on the field,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.72,1:23:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接受我的指引\N{\rEn}you once again let me guide you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.08,1:23:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在山丘上，处于弱势\N{\rEn}Our position on the hill is weak,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.72,1:23:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但左侧的树林有敌人看不见的优势\N{\rEn}but the trees to our left give us an advantage the enemy will not see.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.36,1:23:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要我们团结一心\N{\rEn}We can defeat them
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.36,1:23:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,必能战胜\N{\rEn}if we stay united.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.36,1:23:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我的酒都醒了 -狐臭薰天\N{\rEn}-This is one way to clear the ale. -Smell of a thousand armpits.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.88,1:23:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,搞不好他们一闻就跑了\N{\rEn}Aye. Maybe they smelled us and ran away.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.76,1:23:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-也许吧 -谁摸我屁股？\N{\rEn}- Maybe. - Who touched my arse?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.20,1:24:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊\N{\rEn}Oh my God!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.36,1:24:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的天\N{\rEn}Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.48,1:24:33.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,千军万马\N{\rEn}Rather a lot of them, isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.36,1:24:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德？\N{\rEn}Uhtred?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.08,1:24:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德\N{\rEn}Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.76,1:24:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们要怎么办？ -看到那些袋子了吗？\N{\rEn}-How do we face this? -You see these bags?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.84,1:24:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,传给前线的人，快\N{\rEn}Give them to the men on the front line. Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.44,1:25:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听到口令再举盾牌\N{\rEn}Do not raise your shield until you have to.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.72,1:25:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放轻松，别紧张\N{\rEn}Stay at ease. Stay relaxed.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.76,1:25:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别露出不安的表情\N{\rEn}And do not show them we are unsettled.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.40,1:25:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人，他来了\N{\rEn}Lord! He's here.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.76,1:25:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,暴君来了\N{\rEn}Here he comes. The tyrant himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.68,1:25:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了吗？\N{\rEn}Is it done?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.24,1:25:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-退得越远越好 -是\N{\rEn}-Get back as far as you can. -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.64,1:26:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,组成盾墙！\N{\rEn}Shield wall!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.88,1:26:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（布鲁南博尔之战）
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.88,1:26:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（西元937年）
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.44,1:26:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-准备好了吗，混球们？ -来吧\N{\rEn}-Are we ready, arselings? - Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.52,1:26:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都告解完了\N{\rEn}I have taken their confessions.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.92,1:26:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,待会我叫你们往后退\N{\rEn}When I ask you to give ground,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.84,1:26:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就往后退\N{\rEn}do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.96,1:26:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要退到树林后，就是时候了\N{\rEn}When you see the trees in front of you, it will be time.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.04,1:26:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有信心吗？\N{\rEn}Do you think this will work?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.00,1:26:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要是不成功，我们也不会知道\N{\rEn}If it does not, we will not be here to see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.80,1:26:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相信我\N{\rEn}Trust me.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.76,1:26:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听我指令\N{\rEn}And follow.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.72,1:26:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,组成盾墙！\N{\rEn}Shield wall!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.80,1:26:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,组成\N{\rEn}Shield!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.04,1:27:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盾墙！\N{\rEn}Wall!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.40,1:27:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,往后退！\N{\rEn}Step back!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.84,1:27:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后退！\N{\rEn}Back!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.60,1:27:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们在撤退？\N{\rEn}They retreat?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.64,1:27:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们根本还没出手\N{\rEn}Even before we engage?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.04,1:27:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-往后退 -他们知道自己已经输了\N{\rEn}-Step back! - They know they have lost already.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.92,1:27:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我们杀个痛快\N{\rEn}Let's enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.84,1:27:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前进！\N{\rEn}- Forward!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.20,1:27:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以纯净的心侍奉上帝，我要感谢祂\N{\rEn}I thank God, who I serve with pure conscience.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.56,1:27:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝赐予我们勇气、力量\N{\rEn}God hath not given us a spirit of fear, but of power…
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.48,1:27:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱\N{\rEn}…love…
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.76,1:27:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,健全的心灵\N{\rEn}…and of sound mind!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.16,1:27:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿门\N{\rEn}Amen.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.88,1:27:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,往后退！\N{\rEn}Step back!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.04,1:28:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,预备！\N{\rEn}Brace!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.00,1:28:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重整阵形！冲锋！\N{\rEn}Re-form! Charge!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.16,1:28:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,萨克逊混帐！\N{\rEn}Saxon bastards!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.80,1:28:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,皮尔里各！\N{\rEn}Pyrlig!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.40,1:28:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不！\N{\rEn}No!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.48,1:28:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,皮尔里各\N{\rEn}Pyrlig!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.28,1:29:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们两步，你们一步，听我口令！\N{\rEn}-Two paces! One pace! -Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.48,1:29:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祈祷会成功吧\N{\rEn}-On my command! - Let's hope this works!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.80,1:29:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,退后两步！\N{\rEn}Two paces back!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.24,1:29:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,退后！\N{\rEn}Back!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.04,1:29:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,退后！\N{\rEn}Step back!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.48,1:29:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,退后一步！\N{\rEn}One pace back!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.56,1:29:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们退缩了，我们占上风\N{\rEn}They back off. We have them.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.24,1:29:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-找出国王！\N{\rEn}-Find the king! - Find the king!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.28,1:29:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后退！\N{\rEn}Step back!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.68,1:29:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,往后退！\N{\rEn}Go backwards!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.40,1:29:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为昔得兰而战！\N{\rEn}For Shetland!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.72,1:29:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为奥克尼而战！\N{\rEn}For Orkney!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.56,1:29:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,往后\N{\rEn}Step back!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.44,1:30:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-继续退！\N{\rEn}-Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.44,1:30:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后退！\N{\rEn}Back!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.92,1:30:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保持阵形！\N{\rEn}Protect the line! Protect the line!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.80,1:30:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,退后！\N{\rEn}Step back!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.16,1:30:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再往后退我们就要被占领了\N{\rEn}They'll overrun us if we keep giving ground!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.84,1:30:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,侧翼在搞什么？\N{\rEn}What are they doing along the flank?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.44,1:30:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,传话出去，艾索斯坦就在我们前面\N{\rEn}Send a message that Aethelstan is in front of us!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.32,1:30:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,往后退！\N{\rEn}Step back!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.36,1:30:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,退后！\N{\rEn}Step back!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.84,1:30:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人，阵形正在改变\N{\rEn}The line's turning, Lord. We're coming around!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.36,1:30:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人，艾索斯坦在苏格兰前线\N{\rEn}Aethelstan is on the Scots' line, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.20,1:30:34.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,野猪阵\N{\rEn}Swine wedge!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.24,1:30:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,往后退！\N{\rEn}Step back!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.68,1:30:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,野猪阵！\N{\rEn}Swine wedge!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.64,1:30:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安拉夫，住手！\N{\rEn}Anlaf! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.08,1:30:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前进！\N{\rEn}Push forward!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.72,1:30:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们要抓艾索斯坦！\N{\rEn}They're going for Aethelstan!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.40,1:30:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,往后！\N{\rEn}Step back!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.76,1:31:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后退！\N{\rEn}Back!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.76,1:31:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盾墙撑不住了！\N{\rEn}The wall will not hold!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.32,1:31:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦，保持阵形！\N{\rEn}Aethelstan, hold the line!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.08,1:31:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还要多久，大人？快了\N{\rEn}- How much longer, Lord? - We're almost there.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.96,1:31:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们要攻破艾索斯坦的阵形了\N{\rEn}They're breaking through Aethelstan's line, Lord!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.32,1:31:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们撑不住了\N{\rEn}We can't hold!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.88,1:31:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后退！\N{\rEn}Step back!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.08,1:31:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前进！\N{\rEn}Push forward!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.36,1:31:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人\N{\rEn}Lord!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.32,1:31:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人\N{\rEn}Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.44,1:31:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保护国王！\N{\rEn}Protect the king!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.56,1:32:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}Aethelstan!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.56,1:32:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人，树林！\N{\rEn}Lord, trees!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.40,1:32:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阵形完成了，大人\N{\rEn}We've turned them, Lord! We've turned the line.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.24,1:32:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-发出信号 -是，大人\N{\rEn}- Give the signal! - Yes, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.32,1:32:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-不太对劲 -阵形变换了\N{\rEn}-Something's not right. - We've been turned around!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.64,1:32:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让开\N{\rEn}Make way! Make way!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.92,1:32:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德大人下令了\N{\rEn}Lord Uhtred orders the signal.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.80,1:32:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,攻击！\N{\rEn}Attack!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.84,1:33:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小心后面！\N{\rEn}Behind!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.84,1:33:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去抓国王！\N{\rEn}Hunt down their kings!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.00,1:33:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是陷阱！\N{\rEn}It's a trap!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.96,1:33:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的儿子\N{\rEn}My son!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.12,1:34:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不！\N{\rEn}No!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.00,1:34:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,防守！\N{\rEn}Guards!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.12,1:34:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,撤退！\N{\rEn}Fall back! Fall back!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.60,1:34:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,苏格兰军撤退！\N{\rEn}Scots! Fall back!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.72,1:34:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyah!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.08,1:35:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦\N{\rEn}Aethelstan!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.32,1:36:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾索斯坦！\N{\rEn}Aethelstan!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.52,1:36:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,皮尔里各？\N{\rEn}Pyrlig?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.76,1:37:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那天，五位国王落荒而逃\N{\rEn}Five kings escaped the field that day,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.52,1:37:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们的儿子\N{\rEn}but their sons,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.84,1:37:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,则战死沙场 包括奥克尼、曼岛、昔得兰\N{\rEn}Orkney, Man, Shetland,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.68,1:37:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,斯特拉斯克莱德和苏格兰\N{\rEn}Strathclyde, and Scotland, did not.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.28,1:37:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里每个人\N{\rEn}Each man here
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.44,1:37:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都丢下了一位继承人！\N{\rEn}has left behind an heir.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.56,1:37:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,稍安勿躁\N{\rEn}We wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.00,1:37:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要趁他们撤离时进攻 救回亲人的尸体\N{\rEn}Then attack those leaving the field and return for our kin.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.16,1:38:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别傻了，安拉夫\N{\rEn}Do not be any more foolish, Anlaf.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.32,1:38:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,昔得兰？\N{\rEn}Shetland?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.60,1:38:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不去送死\N{\rEn}No more death.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.32,1:38:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,奥克尼，我们必须战斗！\N{\rEn}Orkney, we need to fight!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.56,1:38:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有什么意义吗？\N{\rEn}What is there to fight for?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.44,1:38:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我需要一艘船回爱尔兰\N{\rEn}I need a ship to get back to Irland.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.76,1:38:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你呢？\N{\rEn}You?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.00,1:38:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大人！\N{\rEn}Lord!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.24,1:38:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德！\N{\rEn}Uhtred!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.36,1:38:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德\N{\rEn}Uhtred!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.44,1:38:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿，嘿，你。\N{\rEn}Hey. Hey, you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.40,1:39:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,费南\N{\rEn}Finan! Finan!
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.84,1:39:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（这场战役是该岛史上 往生者人数最多的一次）
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.00,1:39:22.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（剑伤占死因之首）
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.36,1:39:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（《盎格鲁萨克逊编年史》）
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.20,1:39:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你曾付出真心吗？\N{\rEn}Was any of it real?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.28,1:39:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我实话\N{\rEn}Tell me the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.56,1:39:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告解完了再去见上帝吧\N{\rEn}When you find yourself before God, you will have confessed.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.48,1:39:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的确喜欢上你\N{\rEn}I grew fond of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.28,1:39:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-但我更爱我的族人 -我为了你背叛了自己人\N{\rEn}-But my love for my people prevailed. -I chose you over my people.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.48,1:39:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许我的众神比你的上帝更强大\N{\rEn}Perhaps my gods are stronger than yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.92,1:40:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那为什么是我活着？\N{\rEn}Then why am I living…
Dialogue: 0,1:40:02.68,1:40:03.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你却面临死亡？\N{\rEn}and you about to die?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.76,1:40:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,命运深不可测\N{\rEn}Only fools try to understand destiny.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.68,1:42:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德\N{\rEn}Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.64,1:42:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我儿子还活着吗？\N{\rEn}Did my son survive?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.80,1:42:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是的\N{\rEn}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.04,1:42:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贝班堡又是我们的了\N{\rEn}And Bebbanburg is ours again.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.88,1:42:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们要用石头重建贝班堡 -未来充满希望\N{\rEn}-We will rebuild in stone. - There is so much future.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.48,1:42:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,撑下去，乌特雷德\N{\rEn}Stay with us, Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.12,1:42:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-敌人呢？ -我们打赢了\N{\rEn}-What of the enemy? - The victory is ours.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.12,1:42:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,五名国王之子战死沙场\N{\rEn}Five sons of kings lay dead upon the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.76,1:42:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-五位无冕国王 -“七王丧钟”\N{\rEn}-Five kings that will never be crowned. - "Seven kings must die."
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.32,1:42:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,预言错了，大人\N{\rEn}The prophecy was wrong, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.64,1:42:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加上威塞克斯的爱德华国王 就是六王了\N{\rEn}With Edward of Wessex, it makes six.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.12,1:42:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是第七个吗？\N{\rEn}Am I to be the seventh?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.48,1:42:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经吩咐编年史家记录你的胜利 乌特雷德\N{\rEn}I have told the chroniclers to write of your victory, Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.52,1:42:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想被写进你们的历史\N{\rEn}I have no wish to be written into your history.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.92,1:43:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只想因为信守誓言而进入英灵殿\N{\rEn}I want only to be honored in the feast hall for standing by an oath.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.16,1:43:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,乌特雷德，你不只是支持我\N{\rEn}Uhtred, you did not just stand by me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.08,1:43:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还为了我而战\N{\rEn}You stood for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.72,1:43:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你办到了我所办不到的\N{\rEn}You led where I could not.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.20,1:43:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你原谅了我\N{\rEn}And you forgave me
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.56,1:43:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,即使我罪该万死\N{\rEn}when I was unforgivable.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.80,1:43:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你守护了英格兰的希望\N{\rEn}You saved the hope of England.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.20,1:43:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它一定会在未来实现\N{\rEn}Now in time, it may yet happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.20,1:43:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我曾经说过\N{\rEn}I said that…
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.96,1:43:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你能证明自己是合法的国王\N{\rEn}if you proved yourself to be the rightful king,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.20,1:43:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就会向你称臣\N{\rEn}I would swear Northumbria to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.88,1:44:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,许多人为了英格兰战死沙场\N{\rEn}Men have died fighting under the name of the English.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.44,1:44:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了纪念他们，英格兰应该统一\N{\rEn}To honor them, England should be formed.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.40,1:44:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我有一个条件\N{\rEn}But I have one condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.44,1:44:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你必须宣誓永不结婚\N{\rEn}You must make an oath never to marry.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.48,1:44:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,永不生子\N{\rEn}No heirs.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.64,1:44:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让你弟弟艾德蒙能顺利继承王位\N{\rEn}So your brother Edmund can take the throne unchallenged.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.92,1:44:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\N{\rEn}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.84,1:44:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我向你发誓\N{\rEn}This oath I shall swear.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.08,1:44:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我们将称臣于你\N{\rEn}Then we submit to you as our king.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.16,1:44:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你将成为威塞克斯、麦西亚\N{\rEn}Which makes you ruler of Wessex, Mercia, East Anglia,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.12,1:45:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,东盎格利亚和诺桑比亚的统治者\N{\rEn}and Northumbria.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.92,1:45:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的领土叫做\N{\rEn}And I call my lands
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.84,1:45:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格兰\N{\rEn}England.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.48,1:45:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国王万岁\N{\rEn}Long live the king!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.84,1:45:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国王万岁\N{\rEn}Long live the king.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.12,1:45:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,英格兰国王万岁\N{\rEn}Long live the King of England.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.08,1:45:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回房休息吧，大人\N{\rEn}Return to your chamber, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.92,1:45:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别为我难过\N{\rEn}Do not grieve for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.88,1:45:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的天命是战死沙场\N{\rEn}It was always written that I would fall in battle.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.28,1:45:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不会死的，大人\N{\rEn}You're not gonna die, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.16,1:45:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就逃过死劫，所以…\N{\rEn}-I would go first, and I'm still alive…
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.12,1:45:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对\N{\rEn}So,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.64,1:45:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天命不可违\N{\rEn}destiny is all.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.64,1:47:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,七王死了吗？\N{\rEn}Did seven kings die?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.80,1:47:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,编年史并未记录乌特雷德大人的生死\N{\rEn}The chronicles do not record if my lord Uhtred survived.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.80,1:47:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但所有认识他的人\N{\rEn}But those like me, who knew him,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.80,1:47:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都视他为这个时代最伟大的战士\N{\rEn}recognize him as the greatest warrior of our age,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.60,1:47:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及建国功臣\N{\rEn}and a man who made a kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.76,1:47:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（艾索斯坦统治了15年）
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.20,1:47:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（他被公认为中世纪英格兰 第一位且最伟大的国王）
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.44,1:47:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（丹麦人持续入侵英格兰）
Dialogue: 0,1:47:38.32,1:47:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（直到1066年 被自己的诺曼后裔征服为止）
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.72,1:47:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（贝班堡的堡垒耸立至今）
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.84,1:47:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（贝班堡）
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.48,1:47:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,（诺森伯兰郡班伯城堡，现今）


